2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fed-scanner-aap-bjp-satyendar-jain-sanjay-raut-chidambaram-1956298-2022-05-31%5C%22%3Eopposition%20leaders%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Almost%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Ftop-stories%2F95-of-political-leaders-investigated-by-cbi-ed-are-opposition-leaders-non-bjp-parties-tell-supreme-court-224653%5C%22%3E95%25%20of%20the%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20probed%20by%20the%20ED%20and%20the%20Central%20Bureau%20of%20Investigation%20against%20political%20leaders%20are%20from%20the%20opposition.%20Although%20the%20ED%20claims%20that%20it%20has%20a%20high%20conviction%20rate%20of%2096%25%2C%20the%20figures%20appear%20to%20be%20misplaced%20if%20one%20factors%20in%20the%20number%20of%20cases%20it%20has%20closed%20since%202005.%20The%20ED%20registered%205%2C906%20cases%20until%20March%202023%20but%20completed%20the%20probe%20and%20filed%20a%20chargesheet%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fed-is-claiming-it-has-a-high-conviction-rate-but-its-closed-only-25-cases-since-2005%5C%22%3Eonly%201%2C142%20cases%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20out%20of%20which%20it%20has%20disposed%20of%20only%2025%20cases%2C%20a%20mere%200.42%20of%20the%20total%20number%20of%20cases.%20Of%20those%2025%20cases%2C%20the%20ED%20has%20managed%20convictions%20in%2024%20cases%2C%20which%20is%20around%2096%25%20conviction%20rate%20as%20claimed%20by%20the%20agency.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20such%20circumstances%2C%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20agencies%20are%20being%20misused%20has%20gathered%20much%20currency%2C%20especially%20amidst%20high%20polarisation%20in%20Indian%20politics.%20The%20BJP%2C%20instead%20of%20clearing%20the%20doubts%2C%20has%20often%20given%20out%20details%20of%20various%20cases%20even%20before%20the%20ED%20or%20CBI%20has%20publicly%20shared%20them%2C%20lending%20further%20credence%20to%20the%20opposition%E2%80%99s%20claim.%20As%20the%202024%20Lok%20Sabha%20election%20draws%20closer%20by%20the%20day%2C%20the%20polarised%20opinion%20regarding%20such%20targeted%20action%20on%20opposition%20leaders%20will%20only%20escalate%2C%20even%20as%20the%20ED%20raids%20are%20likely%20to%20gather%20more%20pace%2C%20giving%20further%20ammunition%20to%20the%20BJP%20to%20target%20the%20opposition%20leaders.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706674857000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31094824%2FGCwl4RDa8AAe3Dj.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-2024-elections-near-ed-accelerates-actions-against-opposition-leaders%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Jharkhand%20chief%20minister%20Hemant%20Soren%20is%20the%20most%20recent%20opposition%20leader%20to%20allege%20targeted%20harassment%20by%20the%20central%20agency.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fas-2024-elections-near-ed-accelerates-actions-against-opposition-leaders%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22F-16%20fighter%20jet%20crashes%20near%20South%20Korean%20sea%2Cpilot%20ejects%20safely%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706673772000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107278573%2Cimgsize-33216.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ff-16-fighter-jet-crashes-near-south-korean-seapilot-ejects-safely%2Farticleshow%2F107278582.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20US%20Air%20Force%20pilot%20safely%20ejected%20from%20an%20F-16%20fighter%20jet%20that%20crashed%20off%20South%20Korea's%20coast.%20This%20is%20the%20second%20crash%20of%20its%20kind%20in%20less%20than%20two%20months.%20The%20pilot%2C%20who%20remains%20unidentified%2C%20encountered%20an%20unspecified%20in-flight%20emergency%20and%20ejected%20before%20the%20plane%20crashed%20into%20the%20sea.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20WORLD%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ff-16-fighter-jet-crashes-near-south-korean-seapilot-ejects-safely%2Farticleshow%2F107278582.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22World's%20Richest%20Person%20Overpaid%3F%20Elon%20Musk's%20Pay%20Struck%20Down%20By%20Judge%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIn%20throwing%20out%20Elon%20Musk's%20%2455%20billion%20Tesla%20pay%20deal%2C%20a%20Delaware%20judge%20began%20her%20legal%20opinion%20with%20a%20simple%20question%3A%20%26quot%3BWas%20the%20richest%20person%20in%20the%20world%20overpaid%3F%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20about%20a%20year's%20consideration%20and%20200%20pages%20of%20legal%20reasoning%2C%20her%20answer%20was%20clear%3A%20Yes.%20Yes%20he%20was.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChancery%20Court%20Chief%20Judge%20Kathaleen%20St.%20J.%20McCormick%20on%20Tuesday%20agreed%20with%20a%20Tesla%20investor%20who%20claimed%20the%202018%20pay%20package%20failed%20to%20clearly%20show%20what%20was%20required%20of%20Musk%20to%20earn%20the%20money%20and%20that%20the%20board%20was%20rife%20with%20conflicts%20of%20interest%20when%20it%20approved%20the%20deal%20to%20retain%20him%20as%20chief%20executive%20officer.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20ruling%20threatens%20to%20drop%20Musk%20to%20the%20third-richest%20person%20in%20the%20world%2C%20after%20spending%20the%20past%20couple%20of%20years%20as%20No.%201.%20The%20judge's%20decision%20also%20comes%20just%20days%20after%20Musk%20told%20analysts%20he%20wants%20to%20expand%20his%20stake%20in%20the%20electric%20carmaker%20to%20avoid%20being%20ousted%2C%20to%20maintain%20control%20of%20the%20company%20and%20expand%20further%20into%20artificial%20intelligence.%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20are%20some%20takeaways%20from%20the%20judge's%20historic%20opinion%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EBiggest%20Payday%20Ever%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20plan%20is%20the%20largest%20potential%20compensation%20opportunity%20ever%20observed%20in%20public%20markets%20by%20multiple%20orders%20of%20magnitude%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20wrote.%20It%20was%20250%20times%20bigger%20than%20the%20median%20of%20his%20CEO%20peers.%20It%20was%20more%20than%2033%20times%20the%20runner-up%20plan%20-%20Musk's%202012%20compensation.%20The%20judge%20called%20the%20payout%20%26quot%3Ban%20unfathomable%20sum%2C%26quot%3B%20%26quot%3Bhistorically%20unprecedented%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3Bincredible.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20McCormick%20noted%2C%20%26quot%3BMusk%20does%20not%20dally%20in%20the%20conventional%20amenities%20of%20ordinary%20billionaires.%20For%20example%2C%20he%20owns%20only%20one%20home.%26quot%3B%20She%20then%20pointed%20to%20his%20deposition%20where%20he%20testified%3A%20%26quot%3BI%20tried%20to%20put%20it%20on%20Airbnb%2C%20but%20they%20banned%20Airbnb%20in%20Hillsborough.%20They're%20so%20uptight.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EConflicted%20Board%20Members%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20called%20Tesla's%20process%20of%20approving%20the%20pay%20package%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20flawed%26quot%3B%20because%20the%20board%20members%20on%20the%20compensation%20committee%20tasked%20with%20negotiating%20on%20the%20company's%20behalf%20were%20%26quot%3Bbeholden%26quot%3B%20to%20the%20CEO.%20That%20included%20former%20General%20Counsel%20Todd%20Maron%2C%20who%20had%20worked%20as%20Musk's%20divorce%20attorney%3B%20Antonio%20Gracias%2C%20who%20had%20been%20a%20friend%20of%20Musk's%20for%20two%20decades%20and%20vacationed%20with%20him%20regularly%3B%20and%20compensation%20committee%20chair%20Ira%20Ehrenpreis%2C%20who%20had%20a%2015-year%20relationship%20with%20Musk%2C%20the%20judge%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20is%20unsurprising%20that%20there%20was%20no%20meaningful%20negotiation%20over%20any%20of%20the%20terms%20of%20the%20plan%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThey%20did%20not%20take%20a%20position%20'on%20the%20other%20side'%20of%20Musk%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%20%26quot%3BIt%20was%20a%20cooperative%20venture.%20There%20were%20no%20positional%20negotiations.%20Musk%20proposed%20a%20grant%20size%20and%20structure%2C%20and%20that%20proposal%20supplied%20the%20terms%20considered%20by%20the%20compensation%20committee%20and%20the%20board%20until%20Musk%20unilaterally%20lowered%20his%20ask%20six%20months%20later.%20Musk%20did%20not%20seem%20to%20care%20much%20about%20the%20other%20details.%20They%20got%20ironed%20out.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3EFunding%20Mars%20Trips%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20has%20spent%20years%20in%20pursuit%20of%20his%20ambitions%20to%20go%20to%20Mars%20through%20SpaceX%2C%20which%20has%20become%20a%20juggernaut%20in%20the%20commercial%20space%20industry.%20He%20vowed%20to%20use%20options%20from%20the%202018%20package%20to%20fund%20the%20Mars%20colonization%20if%20it%20was%20upheld.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMusk%20testified%20that%20he%20views%20colonizing%20Mars%20as%20part%20of%20his%20ambition%20to%20save%20humanity%2C%20fearing%20that%20artificial%20intelligence%20has%20the%20potential%20of%20reducing%20humans%20to%20%26quot%3Bthe%20equivalent%20of%20a%20house%20cat%26quot%3B%20or%20to%20eliminate%20them%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BColonizing%20Mars%20is%20an%20expensive%20endeavor%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20said.%20%26quot%3BMusk%20believes%20he%20has%20a%20moral%20obligation%20to%20direct%20his%20wealth%20toward%20that%20goal%2C%20and%20Musk%20views%20his%20compensation%20from%20Tesla%20as%20a%20means%20of%20bankrolling%20that%20mission.%26quot%3B%20Citing%20his%20trial%20testimony%2C%20she%20said%20Musk%20views%20his%20work%20at%20Tesla%20as%20worthwhile%20only%20if%20the%20money%20it%20generates%20can%20be%20applied%20to%20%26quot%3Bmaking%20life%20multi-planetary.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Starry%20Eyed'%20Board%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20defending%20Musk's%20compensation%2C%20Tesla%20lawyers%20failed%20to%20explain%20why%20the%20plan%20was%20necessary%20to%20motivate%20the%20CEO%20to%20achieve%20%26quot%3Btransformative%20growth%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said.%20Musk%20had%20no%20intention%20of%20leaving%20Tesla%2C%20and%20his%20ownership%20stake%20was%20sufficient%20motivation%20to%20keep%20him%20focused%20on%20growth%2C%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSwept%20up%20by%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20'all%20upside%2C'%20or%20perhaps%20starry%20eyed%20by%20Musk's%20superstar%20appeal%2C%20the%20board%20never%20asked%20the%20%2455.8%20billion%20question%3A%20Was%20the%20plan%20even%20necessary%20for%20Tesla%20to%20retain%20Musk%20and%20achieve%20its%20goals%3F%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Superstar'%20CEO's%20Control%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20assessing%20whether%20the%20pay%20deal%20was%20properly%20created%2C%20the%20judge%20said%20she%20had%20to%20determine%2C%20%26quot%3BDoes%20Musk%20control%20Tesla%3F%26quot%3B%20%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20earlier%20Delaware%20litigation%20involving%20the%20company%2C%20no%20other%20judge%20had%20sought%20to%20determine%20if%20Musk%20controlled%20Tesla%2C%20so%20McCormick%20vowed%20to%20%26quot%3Bboldly%20go%20where%20no%20man%20has%20gone%20before%26quot%3B%20by%20answering%20the%20question%20and%20whether%20Musk's%20influence%20had%20created%20a%20conflict%20over%20his%20compensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMcCormick%20noted%20Musk%20held%2021.9%25%20of%20Tesla's%20equity%2C%20his%20status%20as%20%26quot%3BSuperstar%20CEO%26quot%3B%20and%20his%20%26quot%3Bextensive%20ties%20with%20the%20persons%20tasked%20with%20negotiating%20on%20Tesla's%20behalf.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAt%20least%20as%20to%20this%20transaction%2C%20Musk%20controlled%20Tesla%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20judge%20said%2C%20calling%20the%20process%20leading%20to%20his%20pay%20deal%20%26quot%3Bdeeply%20flawed.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Unenviable%20Task'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judge%20offered%20kind%20words%20to%20Musk's%20legal%20team%2C%20led%20by%20lawyers%20from%20the%20powerhouse%20firm%20Cravath%2C%20Swaine%20%26amp%3B%20Moore%2C%20who%20were%20%26quot%3Bleft%20with%20the%20unenviable%20task%20of%20proving%20the%20fairness%20of%20the%20largest%20potential%20compensation%20plan%20in%20the%20history%20of%20public%20markets.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIf%20any%20set%20of%20attorneys%20could%20have%20achieved%20victory%20in%20these%20unlikely%20circumstances%2C%20it%20was%20the%20talented%20defense%20attorneys%20here%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BBut%20the%20task%20proved%20too%20tall%20an%20order.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch3%3E%3Cstrong%3ELike%20a%20Defective%20Car%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh3%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20the%20judge%20concluded%20that%20Musk%20and%20Tesla%20had%20failed%20to%20properly%20justify%20the%20huge%20pay%20package%2C%20which%20she%20compared%20to%20a%20flawed%20car%20design.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIn%20the%20final%20analysis%2C%20Musk%20launched%20a%20self-driving%20process%2C%20recalibrating%20the%20speed%20and%20direction%20along%20the%20way%20as%20he%20saw%20fit%2C%26quot%3B%20McCormick%20wrote.%20%26quot%3BThe%20process%20arrived%20at%20an%20unfair%20price.%26quot%3B%20The%20investor%20suing%20to%20block%20the%20plan%2C%20on%20behalf%20of%20Tesla%20and%20its%20investors%2C%20%26quot%3Brequests%20a%20recall%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said%20before%20granting%20it.%20%26quot%3BThe%20plaintiff%20is%20entitled%20to%20rescission.%26quot%3B%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706673480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-01%2Fdag7u9fo_elon-musk-bloomberg_625x300_30_January_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fw