20making%20big%20announcements%20in%20such%20interim%20budgets.%20Finance%20minister%20Nirmala%20Sitharaman%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fbusiness%2Fno-spectacular-announcement-februarys-interim-budget-finance-minister-9058941%2F%5C%22%3Ehas%20also%20asserted%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20budget%20will%20not%20have%20any%20%E2%80%9Cspectacular%20announcements%E2%80%9D.%20Yet%2C%20interim%20budgets%20do%20have%20considerable%20signalling%20value%20on%20the%20eve%20of%20elections.%20In%202019%2C%20the%20Modi%20government%20used%20the%20opportunity%20to%20make%20a%20major%20announcement%20about%20cash%20transfer%20to%20farmers%20(PM%20Kisan%20Yojana).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHence%20the%20public%20and%20markets%20will%20keenly%20watch%20whether%20the%20lure%20of%20elections%20will%20induce%20the%20government%20to%20make%20grand%20announcements%20or%20even%20depart%20from%20its%20entrenched%20policies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20concern%20before%20the%20government%20is%20managing%20the%20fiscal%20deficit.%20During%20the%20UPA%20government%2C%20commentators%20argued%20that%20it%20ran%20an%20unsustainably%20high%20fiscal%20deficit.%20However%2C%20between%202004%20and%202014%2C%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20averaged%204.63%25%20whereas%20it%20has%20averaged%205.13%25%20under%20the%20NDA.%20For%20both%20UPA%20and%20NDA%2C%20the%20rise%20in%20fiscal%20deficit%20was%20necessitated%20by%20crises%20%E2%80%93%20the%20global%20financial%20crisis%20of%202008%20and%20COVID-19%20respectively.%20However%2C%20when%20one%20examines%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20together%20with%20debt%20data%2C%20it%20makes%20for%20a%20somber%20read.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Cspan%3E%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22What%20the%20Interim%20Union%20Budget%20Might%20Bring%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Context%20in%20Which%20to%20Judge%20it%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwhat-the-interim-union-budget-might-bring-and-the-context-in-which-to-judge-it%5C%22%3EWhat%20the%20Interim%20Union%20Budget%20Might%20Bring%20%E2%80%93%20and%20the%20Context%20in%20Which%20to%20Judge%20it%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20has%20been%20a%20sharp%20uptick%20in%20the%20gross%20debt%20to%20GDP%20ratio%2C%20crossing%20the%2080%25%20mark%20and%20inviting%20concern%20from%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20that%20the%20ratio%20could%20cross%20100%25%20by%202027.%20The%20Union%20government%20is%20expected%20to%20respond%20to%20the%20debt%20concerns%20and%20bring%20down%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20to%204.5%25%20by%202026%20(it%20was%205.9%25%20in%202023-24).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFiscal%20deficits%20can%20be%20reduced%20by%20raising%20tax%20revenue%20and%20reducing%20subsidies.%20The%20tax%20to%20GDP%20ratio%20has%20increased%20by%201%25%2C%20propelled%20largely%20by%20an%20increase%20in%20indirect%20taxes.%20A%20consistent%20feature%20of%20the%20NDA%20government%20has%20been%20sharp%20reduction%20in%20subsidies.%20In%202013-14%2C%20Union%20government%20subsidies%20accounted%20for%202.27%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20These%20now%20stand%20at%201.34%25%20in%202023-24.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20same%20period%2C%20capital%20expenditure%20has%20doubled%20from%201.67%25%20to%203.32%25.%20Post%20the%20COVID-19%20pandemic%2C%20the%20government%20allocated%20increasing%20sums%20towards%20capital%20expenditure.%20The%20stated%20logic%20being%20that%20this%20investment%20will%20create%20jobs%20and%20in%20turn%20raise%20demand.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20the%20ardent%20supporters%20of%20trickle-down%20economics%20privately%20admit%20that%20this%20reliance%20on%20capital%20expenditure%20is%20not%20bearing%20fruits.%20The%20same%20sentiment%20is%20expressed%20regarding%20the%20Production%20Linked%20Incentive%20(PLI)%20scheme.%20Despite%20multiple%20revisions%20and%20handsome%20incentives%2C%20the%20manufacturing%20sector%20has%20not%20taken%20off.%20The%20manufacturing%20growth%20rate%20has%20averaged%205.9%25%20since%202013-14%2C%20the%20share%20of%20manufacturing%20has%20remained%20stagnant%20and%20was%20at%2016.4%25%20in%202022-23%2C%20and%20manufacturing%20jobs%20halved%20between%202016%20and%202021.%20The%20decade%20of%20Make%20in%20India%20saw%20the%20share%20of%20manufacturing%20in%20the%20workforce%20decline%20from%2012.6%25%20in%202011-12%20to%2011.6%25%20in%202021-22.%20Make%20in%20India%20and%20now%20PLI%20have%20failed%20to%20enthuse%20MSMEs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20spectacular%20failure%20on%20the%20part%20of%20the%20government%20is%20disinvestment.%20While%20it%20did%20sell%20Air%20India%20to%20Tatas%2C%20it%20has%20had%20a%20dismal%20track%20record%20overall.%20To%20make%20matters%20worse%2C%20public%20assets%20have%20been%20handed%20over%20to%20select%20groups%20inviting%20concerns%20from%20competitors%20and%20public%20sector%20employees.%20The%20proposed%20national%20monetisation%20pipeline%20has%20also%20failed%20to%20yield%20results.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20job%20market%20remains%20depressing%2C%20especially%20for%20the%20youth.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flabour%2Fyouth-unemployment-on-rise-attributed-largely-to-rural-joblessness-cmie%5C%22%3ECentre%20for%20Monitoring%20Indian%20Economy%20notes%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20unemployment%20rate%20in%20the%20age%20group%2020-24%20years%20was%2044.5%25%20in%20the%20October-December%202023%20quarter.%20For%20the%20age-group%2025-29%20years%2C%20it%20was%20at%20a%2014%20month%20high%20of%2014.33%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20adversity%20of%20the%20job%20market%20is%20matched%20by%20the%20distress%20in%20rural%20India%20where%20the%20demand%20for%20MGNREGA%20has%20reached%20record%20highs.%20Stagnant%20farmer%20income%20and%20falling%20rural%20wages%20at%20a%20time%20when%20stock%20markets%20are%20soaring%2C%20and%20billionaire%20wealth%20balloons%2C%20is%20an%20indictment%20of%20this%20government%E2%80%99s%20priorities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EWatch%3A%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%20noreferrer%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Fwatch-is-it-true-that-the-modi-govt-has-lifted-24-8-crore-people-out-of-poverty%5C%22%20title%3D%5C%22Watch%3A%20Is%20it%20True%20That%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Has%20Lifted%2024.8%20Crore%20People%20Out%20of%20Poverty%3F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3EIs%20it%20True%20That%20the%20Modi%20Govt%20Has%20Lifted%2024.8%20Crore%20People%20Out%20of%20Poverty%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20still%20needs%20large%20scale%20public%20investments%20in%20education%20and%20healthcare.%20Such%20investments%20in%20our%20human%20capital%20have%20great%20potential%20to%20create%20significant%20jobs%20and%20will%20also%20have%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20the%20standard%20of%20living%20of%20our%20citizens.%20A%20key%20landmark%20of%20this%20government%20was%20the%20adoption%20of%20a%20new%20National%20Education%20Policy%20(NEP).%20NEP%202020%20recommends%20that%20investment%20in%20education%20should%20be%206%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20There%20is%20bipartisan%20consensus%20that%20we%20must%20strive%20to%20meet%20the%206%25%20goal.%20However%2C%20expenditure%20on%20education%20has%20been%20less%20than%203%25%20of%20the%20GDP%20over%20the%20last%20decade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20health%20front%2C%20the%20pandemic%20forced%20the%20government%20to%20raise%20healthcare%20expenditure.%20Yet%20there%20has%20been%20a%20rise%20in%20hunger%20and%20malnutrition%2C%20a%20reflection%20of%20the%20larger%20economic%20downturn%20being%20experienced%20by%20a%20substantial%20portion%20of%20our%20population.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.globalhungerindex.org%2Findia.html%5C%22%3EIndia%20is%20ranked%20111th%C2%A0of%20125%3C%2Fa%3E%20countries%20on%20the%20Global%20Hunger%20Index.%20Instead%20of%20addressing%20the%20issue%2C%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20response%20has%20been%20to%20reject%20any%20such%20adverse%20findings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20key%20legacy%20of%20this%20government%20has%20been%20fudging%20data%20and%20on%20other%20occasions%20suppressing%20statistics.%20This%20started%20with%20the%20refusal%20to%20publish%20the%20GDP%20back%20series%20as%20it%20showed%20that%20the%20UPA%20performed%20exceedingly%20well.%20Instead%2C%20a%20new%20series%20was%20commissioned%20that%2C%20confoundingly%2C%20revised%20the%20UPA%20growth%20rates%20downwards.%20Similar%20tactics%20were%20employed%20when%20the%20COVID%20fiscal%20package%20was%20announced.%20Contrary%20to%20the%20claims%20of%20government%2C%20the%20fiscal%20component%20of%20the%20package%20was%20around%201%25%20of%20the%20GDP.%20For%20the%20first%20time%20since%201872%2C%20the%20census%20has%20been%20indefinitely%20delayed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20time%20Prime%20Minister%20Modi%20took%20office%2C%20the%20government%20has%20been%20blessed%20with%20benign%20crude%20oil%20prices.%20The%20government%20could%20have%20passed%20on%20some%20of%20that%20benefit%20to%20consumers%20and%20boosted%20consumption%2C%20and%20thereby%20the%20GDP.%20Instead%2C%20the%20government%20has%20consistently%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fenergy%2Fglobal-oil-prices-fall-by-40-50-but-indian-consumers-still-overpaying%5C%22%3Ekept%20petrol%20and%20diesel%20prices%20at%20a%20steady%20higher%20price%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20mopped%20up%20windfall%20profits%20which%20it%20has%20used%20to%20keep%20the%20fiscal%20deficit%20manageable.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%20likes%20to%20proclaim%20that%20India%20is%20the%20fastest%20growing%20economy.%20However%2C%20if%20they%20had%20boosted%20consumption%20by%20passing%20on%20the%20benefits%20of%20lower%20oil%20prices%2C%20how%20much%20higher%20would%20economic%20growth%20have%20been%3F%20That%20is%20the%20sobering%20lesson%20of%20the%20last%20decade%20%E2%80%93%20underachievement%20and%20lost%20potential.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EProfessor%20M.V.%20Rajeev%20Gowda%20is%20the%20Vice%20Chairman%20of%20the%20Karnataka%20Policy%20and%20Planning%20Commission%20and%20heads%20the%20Congress%20party%E2%80%99s%20Research%20Department.%20Akash%20Satyawali%20is%20a%20public%20policy%20professional%20and%20National%20Coordinator%2C%20Congress%20Research%20Department.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706672751000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F31091509%2Flxrcbsv-vVHXeu0YNbk-unsplash.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-economy-modi-government-rule%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22A%20key%20legacy%20of%20this%20government%20has%20been%20fudging%20data%20and%20on%20other%20occasions%20suppressing%20statistics.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Feconomy%2Findia-economy-modi-government-rule%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%222nd%20Test%3A%20India%20may%20play%204%20spinners%20on%20Vizag%E2%80%99s%20black-soil%20turner%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706672471000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107278089%2Cimgsize-58704.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fsports%2Fcricket%2Fengland-in-india%2Find-vs-eng-2nd-test-team-india-may-be-tempted-to-play-four-spinners-and-a-lone-pacer-on-vizags-black-soil-turner%2Farticleshow%2F107278009.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Ashwin%20and%20Axar%20Patel%20will%20obviously%20lead%20the%20Indian%20spin%20attack%20on%20another%20black-soil%20turner%20in%20Vizag%2C%20but%20former%20India%20captain%20Krishnamachari%20Srikkanth%20feels%20India%20should%20play%20the%20two%20other%20spinners%20%E2%80%94%20wrist-spinner%20Kuldeep%20Yadav%20and%20offie%20Washington%20Sundar%20as%20well%20in%20the%20second%20Test.%20England%20took%20a%201-0%20lead%20in%20the%20five-match%20series%20after%20beating%20India%20by%2028%20runs%20in%20the%20opening%20Test%20in%20Hyderabad.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22DWAIPAYAN%20DATTA%22