e%20BCs%20as%20part%20of%20its%20polarisation%20strategies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20the%20Telangana%20Rashtra%20Samiti%20(TRS)%2C%20now%20the%20Bharat%20Rashtra%20Samithi%20(BRS)%2C%20tried%20to%20strike%20an%20emotional%20chord%20with%20the%20BCs%20by%20holding%20%E2%80%98%3Cem%3Eatmeeya%20sammelan%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99%20meetings%20(meetings%20of%20camaraderie)%20with%20different%20castes%20separately%20to%20build%20a%20vote%20bank%20in%20the%20assembly%20and%20parliament%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Congress%20and%20the%20BJP%20were%20found%20wanting%20in%20wooing%20the%20section%20in%20this%20manner.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficial%20sources%20were%20optimistic%20that%20the%20survey%20will%20aid%20in%20revising%20reservations%20for%20BCs%20in%20gram%20panchayats%2C%20zilla%20parishads%20and%20municipalities.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20mobile%20app%20with%20the%20details%20of%20all%20castes%20and%20sub-castes%20will%20be%20created%20for%20enumeration%20and%20care%20will%20be%20taken%20to%20avoid%20the%20charge%20of%20bias%20as%20faced%20by%20the%20Bihar%20government%20in%20its%20survey%2C%20the%20sources%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30173458%2FSammelanam-1024x768.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30173458%2FSammelanam-1024x768.jpeg%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30173458%2FSammelanam-300x225.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30173458%2FSammelanam.jpeg%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694960%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22630%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20BRS%20tried%20to%20strike%20an%20emotional%20chord%20with%20BCs%20with%20their%20%E2%80%98atmeeya%20sammelan%E2%80%99%20meetings.%20Photo%3A%20X%2F%40PuranamSatish.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbihar-caste-census-released-at-63-obc-ebc-groups-set-to-take-pole-position-in-state-politics%5C%22%3EBihar%E2%80%99s%20caste%20survey%3C%2Fa%3E%20showed%20the%20BC%20population%20in%20the%20state%20to%20be%20around%2063%25.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERajya%20Sabha%20member%20and%20prominent%20BC%20leader%20R.%20Krishnaiah%20said%20there%20were%20a%20number%20of%20court%20cases%20challenging%20reservations%20in%20local%20bodies%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20scientific%20data%20about%20the%20population%20of%20BCs.%20Population-based%20allocation%20of%20funds%20for%20corporations%20and%20federations%20assisting%20people%20in%20the%20traditional%20occupations%20of%20their%20castes%20was%20also%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20previous%20BRS%20government%20had%20taken%20up%20a%20one-day%20comprehensive%20household%20survey%20in%20the%20state%20shortly%20after%20assuming%20the%20reins%20in%202014%2C%20but%20its%20report%20had%20never%20seen%20the%20light%20of%20day.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20unofficial%20claims%20put%20the%20population%20of%20SCs%20in%20Telangana%20at%2018%25%2C%20STs%20at%2010%25%2C%20other%20castes%20at%2021%25%20and%20BCs%20at%2051%25%20as%20per%20the%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20led%20to%20a%20demand%20by%20the%20SCs%20to%20hike%20their%20quota%20in%20education%20and%20employment%20to%2018%25%20in%20tune%20with%20their%20population.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20SCs%20led%20by%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fahead-of-telangana-polls-pm-modi-sets-in-motion-madiga-sub-categorisation-process-report%5C%22%3EMadiga%20Reservation%20Porata%20Samiti%20(MRPS)%3C%2Fa%3E%20had%20also%20been%20demanding%20their%20categorisation%20into%20four%20groups%20%E2%80%93%20A%2C%20B%2C%20C%20and%20D%20%E2%80%93%20since%201994.%20The%20categorisation%20was%20implemented%20for%20some%20time%20during%20the%20chief%20ministership%20of%20Chandrababu%20Naidu%20but%20withdrawn%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdespite-caste-survey-politics-is-obc-vote-eluding-india%5C%22%3EDespite%20Caste%20Survey%20Politics%2C%20Is%20OBC%20Vote%20Eluding%20INDIA%3F%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20again%20constituted%20a%20committee%20of%20secretaries%20headed%20by%20the%20cabinet%20secretary%20to%20go%20into%20the%20categorisation%20of%20SCs%20after%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20conceded%20to%20the%20demand%20of%20MRPS%20president%20Manda%20Krishna%20Madiga%20at%20an%20election%20rally%20of%20the%20BJP%20in%20Hyderabad%20for%20the%20weaker%20sections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAided%20by%20the%20survey%2C%20the%20Congress%20could%20hope%20to%20hijack%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20supporting%20the%20demand%20for%20the%20categorisation%20of%20SCs%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections.%20The%20party%20had%20also%20conceded%20to%20the%20demand%20of%2018%25%20reservation%20for%20SCs%20and%20their%20categorisation%20into%20four%20groups%20named%20A%2C%20B%2C%20C%20and%20D%20in%20its%20manifesto.%20It%20also%20promised%20reservations%20for%20minorities%20and%20finance%20corporations%20for%20all%20BC%20castes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20former%20Congress%20minister%20who%20did%20not%20want%20to%20be%20named%20said%20the%20survey%20will%20help%20the%20government%20in%20extending%20largesse%20proportional%20to%20the%20population%20of%20the%20concerned%20groups.%20So%20far%2C%20the%20benefits%20were%20cornered%20by%20dominant%20caste%20groups%20like%20the%20Madigas%20among%20the%20SCs%20and%20the%20Munnuru%20Kapus%20among%20the%20BCs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFormer%20Congress%20Rajya%20Sabha%20member%20V.%20Hanumantha%20Rao%20expected%20the%20SCs%2C%20STs%20and%20BCs%20to%20back%20the%20party%20in%20a%20big%20way%20after%20the%20survey%20as%20%C2%A0an%20equitable%20quota%20system%20would%20be%20in%20place.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-1024x478.png%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22840%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-1024x478.png%201024w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82-300x140.png%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2F16141604%2FThe-Wire-82.png%201200w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-685050%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22392%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EThe%20Congress%20could%20hope%20to%20hijack%20the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20place%20in%20supporting%20the%20demand%20for%20the%20categorisation%20of%20SCs%20ahead%20of%20general%20elections.%20Photo%3A%20Facebook%2FNarendra%20Modi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETelangana%20has%20never%20had%20clean%20data%20on%20the%20socio-economic%20status%20of%20its%20population%20since%201931%2C%20when%20a%20census%20was%20conducted%20during%20British%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20chairman%20of%20the%20Telangana%20State%20Backward%20Classes%20Commission%2C%20V.%20Krishnamohan%20Rao%2C%20has%20warned%20about%20the%20danger%20of%20bias%20in%20the%20survey%20as%20happened%20in%20Bihar%20if%20the%20government%20were%20to%20conduct%20the%20survey%20through%20its%20departments.%20The%20commission%20was%20the%20competent%20authority%20for%20the%20purpose%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20recalled%20that%20a%20socio-economic%20survey%20by%20the%20United%20Progressive%20Alliance-II%20government%20in%202011-14%20at%20a%20cost%20of%20Rs%205%2C000%20crore%20was%20dropped%20by%20the%20subsequent%20BJP%20government%20as%20it%20was%20found%20that%20there%20were%20errors%20with%20regard%20to%20the%20details%20of%20forty%20million%20individuals%20in%20the%20survey%20taken%20up%20by%20the%20Ministry%20of%20Rural%20Development.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Supreme%20Court%20and%20some%20high%20courts%20had%20struck%20down%20the%20surveys%20as%20they%20lacked%20scientific%20validity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKrishnamohan%20Rao%20felt%20that%20social%20indicators%20like%20discrimination%2C%20financial%20status%20and%20the%20representation%20of%20targeted%20groups%20in%20various%20spheres%20could%20be%20thoroughly%20studied%20by%20commissions%20of%20inquiry.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20retired%20bureaucrat%2C%20N.%20Jayaprakash%20Narayan%2C%20dubbed%20the%20survey%20as%20a%20retrograde%20step%20for%20political%20gains.%20It%20was%20nothing%20but%20another%20attempt%20to%20divide%20people%20on%20caste%20lines%20instead%20of%20making%20them%20less%20caste%20conscious%2C%20he%20said%2C%20adding%20that%20reservation%20on%20affirmative%20political%20action%20did%20not%20require%20a%20caste%20survey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20disagreed%20with%20the%20government%E2%80%99s%20claim%20that%20the%20survey%20was%20meant%20to%20identify%20beneficiaries%20for%20its%20welfare%20schemes.%20Better%20selection%20of%20beneficiaries%20was%20unrelated%20to%20caste%20survey%20going%20by%20past%20experience%2C%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706620671000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30182304%2FTelangana-prabhutvam-II.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-congress-govts-preparations-for-caste-survey-in-full-swing-as-lok-sabha-polls-inch-closer%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Official%20sources%20expressed%20optimism%20that%20the%20survey%20would%20help%20revise%20reservations%20for%20the%20state's%20backward%20class%20communities%2C%20while%20others%20cautioned%20against%20accusations%20of%20bias%20or%20said%20the%20exercise%20was%20for%20political%20gain.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A1%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Ftelangana-congress-govts-preparations-for-caste-survey-in-full-swing-as-lok-sabha-polls-inch-closer%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Dissecting%20Modi's%20Pre-Poll%20Visits%20to%20the%20South%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30165616%2FEffect-91.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3EThis%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2Fp%2Fviksit-yatras-emerging-as-bjp-election%5C%22%3Epiece%3C%2Fa%3E%20was%20first%20published%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3EThe%20India%20Cable%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ci%3E%C2%A0%E2%80%93%C2%A0a%20premium%20newsletter%20from%C2%A0The%20Wire%20%26amp%3B%20Galileo%20Ideas%20%E2%80%93%20and%20has%20been%20republished%20here.%20To%20subscribe%20to%20The%20India%20Cable%2C%C2%A0%3C%2Fi%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.theindiacable.com%2F%5C%22%3E%3Ci%3Eclick%20here%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ci%3E.%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArrival%20at%20a%20hurriedly%20built%20helipad%2C%20a%20road%20show%20along%20the%20way%2C%20temple%20visits%2C%20a%20BJP%20workers%E2%80%99%20meeting%20or%20public%20rally%2C%20announcing%20central%20schemes%20for%20the%20respective%20state%20and%20finally%20inaugurating%20a%20couple%20of%20Union%20government%20programmes.%20This%20is%20the%20standard%20itinerary%20for%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ongoing%20southern%20forays.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20has%20already%20covered%20temples%20like%20Tirupathi%20and%20Veerbhadra%20in%20Andhra%20Pradesh%2C%20Ranganathswamy%20and%20Rameshwaram%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20and%20Guruvayur%20and%20Thriprayar%20in%20Kerala.%20At%20all%20these%20places%2C%20he%20had%20road%20shows%20and%20political%20meetings.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20present%20schedule%2C%20about%20140%20Modi%20rallies%20have%20been%20lined%20up%20across%20the%20country%20during%20the%20next%20three%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWeeks%20before%20a%20PM%20visit%2C%20the%20first%20thing%20the%20security%20officials%20do%20is%20to%20persuade%20the%20media%20not%20to%20carry%20adverse%20reports%20and%20the%20details%20of%20security%20measures%20in%20%E2%80%98national%20interest.%E2%80%99%20Thus%2C%20people%20come%20to%20know%20about%20the%20rigorous%20traffic%20restrictions%20and%20omnipresent%20barricades%20only%20when%20they%20appear%20along%20the%20long%20stretch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20many%20as%2022%2C000%20police%20personnel%20were%20deployed%20in%20Chennai%20when%20Modi%20came%20to%20participate%20in%20the%20Khelo%20India%20Youth%20games%20as%20part%20of%20a%20five-layer%20security%20for%20the%20PM.%20This%20is%20in%20addition%20to%20the%20SPG%20and%20an%20army%20of%20security%20personnel.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30170059%2FGEN1cm9bIAAMIAu.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221137%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30170059%2FGEN1cm9bIAAMIAu.jpg%201137w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30170059%2FGEN1cm9bIAAMIAu-284x300.jpg%20284w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30170059%2FGEN1cm9bIAAMIAu-970x1024.jpg%20970w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694954%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20at%20the%20inauguration%20of%20Khelo%20India%20Youth%20Games%20in%20Chennai%20on%20January%2019%2C%202024.%20Photo%3A%20X%20(Twitter)%2F%40narendramodi.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20Srirangam%2C%20it%20was%203%2C500%20plus%20security%20paraphernalia.%20At%20Guruvayur%2C%202%2C000%20police%20personnel%20were%20deployed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20level%20of%20security%20for%20former%20PMs%2C%20including%20Vajpayee%20during%20the%20Kargil%20war%2C%20was%20a%20fraction%20of%20what%20Modi%20has.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Guruvayur%2C%20traffic%20halted%20on%20all%20artery%20roads%20to%20the%20temple%20town%20for%20about%20ten%20kms%20for%2018%20hours%20before%20Modi%20arrived%20at%20a%20helipad%20hurriedly%20built%20at%20a%20school%20ground.%20There%20was%20also%20a%20rehearsal%20before%20this.%20This%20meant%20about%20a%20hundred%20vehicles%2C%20some%20from%20outside%20the%20state%2C%20held%20up%20outside%20the%20sanitized%20periphery.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFour%20governors%20of%20southern%20states%20had%20also%20come%20to%20meet%20Modi.%20Their%20security%20also%20added%20to%20the%20disruption.%20Traffic%20police%20had%20announced%20details%20of%20traffic%20diversions%20at%20the%20last%20minute.%20Buses%20along%20the%20route%20carrying%20officegoers%20in%20the%20morning%20got%20delayed.%20Due%20to%20diversions%2C%20many%20passengers%20were%20told%20to%20get%20down%20at%20odd%20places%20far%20away%20from%20their%20destinations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20mainstream%20media%20played%20it%20safe%2C%20parallel%20media%20had%20graphic%20details%20of%20patients%20who%20were%20held%20up%20on%20their%20way%20to%20the%20general%20hospital%20at%20Kochi.%20At%20all%20places%2C%20the%20first%20sign%20of%20a%20Modi%20roadshow%20is%20the%20appearance%20of%20barricades.%20At%20Kochi%2C%20the%20barricades%20put%20up%20prevented%20egress%20and%20ingress%20of%20the%20residents%20until%20Modi%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESince%20the%20roadshow%20was%20in%20the%20evening%2C%20it%20held%20up%20a%20large%20number%20of%20those%20returning%20home%20from%20the%20offices.%20The%20disruption%20of%20public%20transport%20made%20it%20worse.%20Many%20had%20to%20walk%20long%20distances.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Guruvayur%20Krishna%20temple%20is%20a%20preferred%20place%20for%20initiation%20of%20rice%20feeding%20for%20babies%2C%3Cem%3E%20tulabharam%3C%2Fem%3E%20and%20weddings%20%E2%80%94%20a%20practice%20which%20began%20in%20the%20mid-20th%20century%20and%20can%20be%20traced%20to%20church%20marriages.%20Rice%20feeding%20and%20tulabharam%20were%20cancelled%20for%20the%20day%20due%20to%20the%20Modi%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThousands%20of%20devotees%2C%20who%20visit%20the%20temple%20from%20faraway%20places%2C%20had%20to%20wait%20outside%20the%20three-layer%20security%20or%20cancel%20it%20on%20that%20auspicious%20day.%20Sabarimala%20pilgrims%2C%20who%20were%20returning%20from%20the%20hill%20temple%20after%20the%20Makaravilakku%2C%20usually%20visit%20Guruvayur.%20Most%20of%20the%20pilgrim%20groups%20had%20to%20cancel%20their%20visit%20or%20wait%20for%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20departure.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOver%2080%20marriages%20were%20scheduled%20that%20day.%20At%20the%20last%20minute%2C%2031%20of%20these%20were%20rescheduled%20between%20as%20early%20as%205%20am%20and%206%20am%2C%20a%20safe%20two%20hours%20before%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20arrival.%20Among%20them%20was%20a%20couple%20I%20know%20from%20Vadakkancheri%20whose%20wedding%20was%20originally%20scheduled%20between%208%20am%20and%209%20am.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20pleading%20with%20the%20Devaswam%20board%20chairman%2C%20they%20got%20it%20rescheduled%20between%205%20am%20and%206%20am.%20Adding%20to%20their%20woes%2C%20the%20SPG%20allowed%20only%20four%20persons%20to%20attend.%20The%20groom%E2%80%99s%20and%20brides%E2%80%99%20parties%20had%20invited%20a%20large%20number%20of%20friends%20and%20relatives.%20All%20invitees%2C%20including%20NRI%20relatives%20who%20had%20come%20from%20abroad%2C%20had%20to%20sit%20outside%20the%20three-layer%20security%20ring.%20Reaching%20at%2012%20midnight%2C%20the%20parents%20had%20a%20harrowing%20time%20to%20get%20the%20entry%20passes%20to%20the%20temple.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEven%20after%20the%20ceremony%20at%20the%20temple%2C%20the%20parties%20were%20held%20up%20inside%20the%20complex%20as%20the%20SPG%20insisted%20they%20could%20leave%20only%20after%20Modi%20left.%20This%20meant%20they%20were%20held%20up%20for%20five%20hours.%20Earlier%2C%20two%20other%20marriage%20parties%20cancelled%20their%20wedding%20and%20left%20Guruvayur%20in%20a%20huff.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDue%20to%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20visit%2C%20the%20Guruvayur%20municipality%20and%20adjoining%20five%20panchayats%20closed%20all%20educational%20institutions.%20The%20SPG%20asked%20all%20guest%20houses%20and%20hotels%20to%20provide%20a%20list%20of%20their%20registered%20guests.%20Two%20days%20before%2C%20they%20were%20also%20ordered%20to%20cancel%20all%20registrations%20for%20two%20days%20and%20evict%20the%20guests%20before%20the%20Modi%20visit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmong%20them%20were%20those%20who%20had%20come%20for%20month-long%20observances%20at%20the%20temple.%20Within%20the%20temple%2C%20all%20except%2015%20of%20its%2040-odd%20attendants%20and%20office%20staff%20were%20told%20to%20leave.%20They%20were%20allowed%20in%20only%20after%20Modi%20left.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20strategists%20in%20Delhi%20as%20well%20as%20state%20leaders%20maintain%20that%20each%20Modi%20visit%20to%20Kerala%20has%20helped%20the%20party%20make%20inroads%20into%20new%20sections%20of%20people.%20In%20the%20coming%20months%2C%20Narendra%20Modi%20is%20set%20to%20make%20more%20such%20visits%20to%20Kerala.%20According%20to%20a%20BJP%20leader%2C%20its%20high%20command%20has%20identified%20four%20or%20five%20winnable%20seats.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20party%20in%20the%20past%20was%20never%20able%20to%20win%20a%20parliament%20seat.%20It%20had%20its%20lone%20MLA%20in%20the%20previous%20assembly.%20In%20the%20last%20assembly%20polls%2C%20the%20party%20lost%20that%20seat%20too%20and%20the%20BJP%20drew%20a%20blank.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20current%20Lok%20Sabha%20elections%2C%20it%20is%20concentrating%20on%20Thrissur%20where%20it%20is%20hoping%20to%20rely%20on%20the%20popularity%20of%20an%20actor-turned-politician.%20Apart%20from%20superior%20money%20power%2C%20the%20BJP%20high%20command%20expects%20its%20Christian%20outreach%20will%20bear%20fruit%20and%20enable%20it%20to%20win%20over%20local%20church%20leaders.%20This%20could%20tilt%20the%20balance%20in%20many%20constituencies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EP.%20Raman%20is%20a%20veteran%20journalist%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706619646000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30165616%2FEffect-91.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdissecting-modis-pre-poll-visits-to-the-south%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22As%20per%20the%20present%20schedule%2C%20about%20140%20Modi%20rallies%20have%20been%20lined%20up%20across%20the%20country%20during%20the%20next%20three%20months.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fdissecting-modis-pre-poll-visits-to-the-south%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Record-breaking%20Suits%20and%20Bluey%20named%20most-streamed%20shows%20of%202023%20in%20US%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706619297000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fichef.bbci.co.uk%2Fnews%2F1024%2Fbranded_news%2F8598%2Fproduction%2F_132500243_gettyimages-841344624.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-68138795%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20legal%20drama%2C%20starring%20the%20future%20Duchess%20of%20Sussex%2C%20enjoyed%20a%20huge%20surge%20in%20popularity%20last%20year.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A37%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-68138795%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-bbc-co-uk.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-68138795.amp%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bbc.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fentertainment-arts-68138795.amp%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Bharatiya%20Nyay%20Sanhita%3A%20Decolonising%20or%20Reinforcing%20Colonial%20Ideas%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11180259%2FUneven.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202023%2C%20the%20Indian%20Parliament%20enacted%20three%20new%20criminal%20codes%E2%80%94the%20Bharatiya%20Nyaya%20Sanhita%20(%E2%80%98BNS%E2%80%99)%2C%20the%20Bharatiya%20Nagrik%20Suraksha%20Sanhita%20(%E2%80%98BNSS%E2%80%99)%20and%20the%20Bharatiya%20Sakshya%20Adhiniyam%20(%E2%80%98BSA%E2%80%99)%E2%80%94to%20replace%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%2C%201860%20(%E2%80%98IPC%E2%80%99)%2C%20the%20Criminal%20Procedure%20Code%2C%201973%20(%E2%80%98CrPC%E2%80%99)%2C%20and%20the%20Indian%20Evidence%20Act%2C%201872%20(%E2%80%98IEA%E2%80%99)%2C%20respectively.%20The%20Bills%20received%20Presidential%20assent%2C%20and%20were%20published%20in%20the%20Official%20Gazette%20on%20December%2025%2C%202023.%20The%20date%20on%20which%20they%20will%20come%20into%20force%20is%20yet%20to%20be%20notified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stated%20aim%20of%20these%20three%20legislations%20is%20to%20%E2%80%98decolonise%E2%80%99%20criminal%20laws%20of%20the%20British%20era.%20The%20Union%20Government%20has%20repeatedly%20invoked%20the%20rhetoric%20of%20decolonisation%2C%20justice%2C%20and%20citizen-centric%20laws%20to%20justify%20this%20legal%20reform%20project.%20To%20assess%20whether%20the%20new%20laws%20succeed%20in%20this%20aim%2C%20we%20must%20first%20articulate%20what%20was%20colonial%20about%20these%20three%20legislations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20piece%20focuses%20on%20the%20BNS%2C%20meant%20to%20replace%20the%20IPC.%20It%20analyses%20how%20the%20bill%20falls%20short%20of%20its%20stated%20goal%20of%20decolonisation.%20We%20argue%20that%20the%20BNS%20expands%20powers%20of%20the%20state%20and%20the%20police%2C%20retains%20offences%20grounded%20in%20archaic%20morality%2C%20and%20widens%20the%20punitive%20network%20through%20broad%20and%20vaguely%20defined%20offences.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EOffences%20against%20the%20state%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20of%20the%20markers%20of%20colonialism%20is%20a%20perpetual%20and%20continued%20expansion%20of%20the%20police%20powers%20that%20the%20State%20exerts%20over%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcore.ac.uk%2Fdownload%2Fpdf%2F235410229.pdf%5C%22%3Esubjects%3C%2Fa%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcore.ac.uk%2Fdownload%2Fpdf%2F235410229.pdf%5C%22%3E.%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0The%20new%20criminal%20laws%20do%20little%20to%20steer%20away%20from%20the%20colonial%20mentality%20of%20an%20all-powerful%20state.%20Rather%2C%20by%20expanding%20police%20powers%20and%20creating%20provisions%20for%20vaguely%20defined%20but%20stringently%20punished%20offences%2C%20they%20deepen%20the%20power%20dynamic%20between%20state%20and%20citizen.%20In%20this%20regard%2C%20perhaps%20the%20most%20significant%20vestige%20of%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20laws%20is%20the%20IPC%E2%80%99s%20chapter%2C%20%E2%80%98Offences%20Against%20the%20State%E2%80%99%2C%20which%20includes%20the%20offence%20of%20sedition%20under%20Section%20124A.%20While%20the%20chapter%20remains%20largely%20unchanged%20in%20the%20BNS%2C%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20replaced%20by%20a%20new%20offence%2C%20defined%20in%20section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%2C%20titled%20%E2%80%98Act%20endangering%20sovereignty%2C%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India%E2%80%99%20and%20differs%20in%20some%20ways%20from%20its%20counterpart%20in%20the%20IPC.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESection%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20focuses%20on%20activities%20that%20excite%20hatred%2C%20contempt%20or%20disaffection%20towards%20the%20government%2C%20whereas%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%20penalises%20activities%20that%20excite%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20encourage%20%E2%80%98feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20endanger%20the%20%E2%80%98sovereignty%20or%20unity%20and%20integrity%20of%20India.%E2%80%99%20While%20the%20word%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20removed%20from%20the%20penal%20statute%2C%20the%20new%20provision%20appears%20to%20be%20as%20rights-restrictive%20as%20its%20counterpart.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20BNS%20does%20not%20explain%20what%20constitutes%20exciting%20%E2%80%98subversive%20activities%E2%80%99%20or%20encouraging%20%E2%80%98feelings%20of%20separatist%20activities%E2%80%99.%20Post-independence%2C%20courts%20have%20had%20multiple%20occasions%20to%20interpret%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20particularly%20regarding%20its%20impact%20on%20the%20right%20to%20freedom%20of%20speech%20guaranteed%20under%20the%20Constitution.%20These%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F111867%2F%5C%22%3Edecisions%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0have%20had%20the%20effect%20of%20limiting%20the%20scope%20of%20the%20section%20to%20only%20curb%20speech%20that%20poses%20an%20imminent%20threat%20to%20public%20order.%20In%20this%20light%2C%20the%20scope%20of%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%E2%80%94a%20completely%20new%20provision%20with%20changed%20standards%E2%80%94is%20unclear%20since%20the%20tests%20evolved%20by%20the%20courts%20in%20decisions%20regarding%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20no%20longer%20apply.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20title%3D%5C%22Second%20Avatar%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20The%20Key%20Changes%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fsecond-avatar-criminal-law-bills-has-anything-changed%5C%22%3ESecond%20Avatar%20of%20the%20Criminal%20Law%20Bills%3A%20The%20Key%20Changes%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Union%20government%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Findia%2Fsedition-to-go-but-endangering-unity-and-integrity-of-india-could-result-in-life-term%2Farticleshow%2F102661307.cms%3Ffrom%3Dmdr%5C%22%3Ereasoned%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0that%20the%20new%20provision%20no%20longer%20criminalises%20%E2%80%98sedition%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Erajdroh%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20but%20criminalises%20%E2%80%98treason%E2%80%99%20(%3Cem%3Edeshdroh%3C%2Fem%3E)%2C%20since%20criticising%20the%20government%20is%20no%20longer%20an%20offence.%20However%2C%20this%20does%20not%20signify%20a%20departure%20from%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Explanation%20to%20Section%20124A%20of%20the%20IPC%20in%20any%20case%20exempts%20from%20its%20ambit%20any%20comments%20criticising%20governmental%20measures%20that%20do%20not%20excite%20feelings%20of%20hatred%20and%20disaffection%20as%20defined%20in%20the%20provision.%20Section%20152%20of%20the%20BNS%20lays%20down%20a%20similar%20exception.%20Thus%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20how%20the%20standards%20under%20the%20new%20provision%20are%20substantially%20different%20from%20those%20under%20the%20older%20provision.%C2%A0Moreover%2C%20the%20concern%20about%20sedition%20law%20has%20always%20been%20about%20how%20the%20state%20has%20utilised%20it%20to%20stifle%20dissent%20through%20arrest%20and%20extended%20detention%20of%20persons.%20Most%20cases%20do%20not%20lead%20to%20conviction%20(as%20reflected%20in%20the%20NCRB%20Data%20for%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2F1702032406TABLE10A7.pdf%5C%22%3E2022%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fpost%2F1679664222TABLE10A7.pdf%5C%22%3E2021%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7-2020.pdf%5C%22%3E2020%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7_1-2019.pdf%5C%22%3E2019%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2F2022%2FJuly%2F11%2Fcustom%2Fcrime-in-india%2Ftable-10A.7-2018.pdf%5C%22%3E2018%3C%2Fa%3E)%2C%20and%20the%20criminal%20process%20itself%20becomes%20the%20punishment.%20This%20has%20been%20facilitated%20by%20broadly%20worded%20provisions%20that%20empower%20law%20enforcement%20agencies%20to%20detain%20individuals.%20Creating%20more%20ambiguity%20in%20the%20standards%20for%20these%20offences%20will%20only%20increase%20their%20harmful%20impact.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ERemnants%20of%20archaic%20moralism%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAn%20important%20sign%20of%20the%20colonial%20legacy%20of%20the%20IPC%20is%20the%20Victorian%20morality%20encoded%20in%20it.%20This%20is%20exemplified%20in%20the%20marital%20rape%20exception%20(Section%20375%2C%20IPC)%20and%20in%20language%20such%20as%20%E2%80%98outraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20a%20woman%E2%80%99%20(Section%20354%2C%20IPC)%2C%20the%20understanding%20of%20obscenity%20(defined%20in%20Section%20292%2C%20IPC)%2C%20and%20the%20criminalisation%20of%20abortion%20(Section%20312%2C%20IPC).%20We%20discuss%20each%20of%20these%20in%20turn.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EException%20to%20marital%20rape%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20marital%20rape%20exception%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findianexpress.com%2Farticle%2Fopinion%2Fcolumns%2Frape-is-rape-no-exceptions%2F%5C%22%3Erooted%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20the%20notion%20of%20irrevocable%20consent%20upon%20marriage.%20This%20was%20first%20articulated%20by%20Matthew%20Hale%2C%20who%20wrote%20that%20it%20is%20impossible%20for%20a%20husband%20to%20be%20guilty%20of%20rape%20upon%20his%20wife%2C%20since%20marriage%20implies%20irrevocable%20consent%20to%20sexual%20intercourse%20on%20her%20part.%20This%20principle%20was%20entrenched%20in%20English%20common%20law%2C%20and%20from%20there%2C%20found%20its%20way%20into%20the%20IPC.%20While%20the%20UK%20House%20of%20Lords%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.bailii.org%2Fuk%2Fcases%2FUKHL%2F1991%2F12.html%5C%22%3Estruck%20down%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20exception%20in%201991%2C%20it%20continued%20to%20remain%20in%20the%20IPC.%20The%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%E2%80%99s%20(2013)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FJustice_Verma_Amendmenttocriminallaw_Jan2013.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommendation%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0to%20remove%20this%20exception%20was%20not%C2%A0%20implemented%20in%20the%20subsequent%20amendment%20of%20the%20IPC.%20Recently%2C%20a%20Division%20Bench%20of%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20delivered%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2Fras11052022cw2842015190346-417219.pdf%5C%22%3Esplit%20verdict%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0in%20a%20petition%20challenging%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20the%20provision%2C%20and%20the%20issue%20is%20currently%20pending%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court.%20Given%20that%20this%20is%20an%20effort%20to%20rid%20our%20criminal%20justice%20system%20of%20colonial%20era%20laws%2C%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20BNS%20would%20have%20been%20the%20perfect%20opportunity%20to%20end%20the%20exception%2C%20and%20recognise%20the%20bodily%20integrity%20and%20sexual%20autonomy%20of%20married%20women.%20However%2C%20the%20BNS%2C%20in%20Section%2063%20(offence%20of%20rape)%20retains%20the%20exception.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EOutraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20women%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20notable%20colonial%20inheritance%20in%20the%20IPC%20is%20the%20use%20of%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99%20in%20Sections%20354%20and%20509%2C%20which%20stem%20from%20a%20patriarchal%20understanding%20of%20sexual%20violence.%20As%20one%20of%20us%20has%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdrive.google.com%2Ffile%2Fd%2F1jZhgimstCgGReUpBANLPu68wbUE7nbqe%2Fview%5C%22%3Eargued%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0elsewhere%2C%20the%20centring%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99%20in%20Section%20354%20of%20the%20IPC%20invariably%20moves%20the%20discussion%20to%20what%20constitutes%20a%20woman%E2%80%99s%20modesty%2C%20and%20whether%20the%20woman%20was%20of%20a%20%E2%80%98modest%20character%E2%80%99%20to%20begin%20with%2C%20so%20as%20to%20be%20able%20to%20claim%20that%20her%20modesty%20was%20outraged.%20This%20deviates%20from%20the%20understanding%20of%20sexual%20assault%20as%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20bodily%20autonomy%20of%20the%20victim%2C%20and%20thus%20allows%20notions%20of%20morality%20to%20inform%20decision%20making%20in%20cases%20of%20sexual%20violence.%20Recognising%20this%2C%20the%20Justice%20Verma%20Committee%20had%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fadrindia.org%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2FJustice_Verma_Amendmenttocriminallaw_Jan2013.pdf%5C%22%3Erecommended%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0the%20redrafting%20and%20rewording%20of%20Section%20354.%20It%20suggested%20that%20references%20to%20%E2%80%98outraging%20the%20modesty%20of%20women%E2%80%99%20be%20removed%20from%20the%20provision%2C%20and%20be%20replaced%20with%20the%20term%20%E2%80%98sexual%20assault%E2%80%99.%20This%20change%20was%20not%20made%20when%20the%20IPC%20was%20amended%20in%202013.%20Implementing%20it%20in%20the%20new%20Code%20would%20have%20represented%20a%20substantive%20departure%20from%20language%20invoking%20colonial%20morality%2C%20based%20on%20notions%20of%20honour%2C%20chastity%2C%20and%20modesty%20in%20our%20laws.%20However%2C%20Sections%2074%20and%2079%20of%20the%20BNS%20retain%20the%20language%20of%20%E2%80%98modesty%E2%80%99.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EObscenity%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20provisions%20regarding%20obscenity%20in%20the%20IPC%20represent%20yet%20another%20instance%20of%20the%20moral%20conservatism%20of%20colonial%20era%20laws.%20Section%20292%20of%20the%20IPC%20penalises%20the%20sale%2C%20exhibition%2C%20publication%2C%20etc.%2C%20of%20any%20obscene%20material%2C%20and%20Section%20294%20penalises%20obscene%20actions%20in%20public.%20The%20test%20for%20determining%20what%20constitutes%20%E2%80%98obscenity%E2%80%99%20under%20these%20sections%20is%20if%20the%20materials%2Factions%20in%20question%20are%20%E2%80%98lascivious%E2%80%99%20or%20appeal%20to%20%E2%80%98prurient%20interests%E2%80%99%20or%20if%20they%20tend%20to%20%E2%80%98deprave%20and%20corrupt%E2%80%99%20people.%20In%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikisource.org%2Fwiki%2FRegina_v._Hicklin%5C%22%3ER%20v.%20Hicklin%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20UK%20House%20of%20Lords%20held%20that%20all%20materials%20which%20have%20a%20tendency%20to%20%E2%80%98deprave%20and%20corrupt%20those%20whose%20minds%20are%20open%20to%20such%20immoral%20influences%E2%80%99%20are%20obscene.%20This%20test%20was%20imported%20into%20Indian%20law%20through%20the%20Supreme%20Court%E2%80%99s%201965%20decision%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1623275%2F%5C%22%3EUdeshi%20v.%20Maharashtra%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20Court%20ruled%20that%20any%20material%20that%20involved%20%E2%80%98treating%20with%20(sic)%20sex%20in%20a%20manner%20appealing%20to%20the%20carnal%20side%20of%20human%20nature%2C%20or%20having%20that%20tendency%E2%80%99%20would%20be%20considered%20obscene.%20This%20implied%20that%20any%20material%20that%20tended%20to%20arouse%20sexual%20feelings%20would%20be%20deemed%20obscene%20within%20the%20meaning%20of%20the%20provision.%20In%202014%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20in%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F195958005%2F%5C%22%3ESarkar%20v.%20West%20Bengal%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0espoused%20a%20slightly%20modified%20test%20for%20obscenity%20called%20the%20%E2%80%98community%20standards%20test%2C%E2%80%99%20stating%20that%20%E2%80%98those%20sex-related%20materials%20which%20have%20a%20tendency%20of%20%E2%80%98exciting%20lustful%20thoughts%E2%80%99%20can%20be%20held%20to%20be%20obscene%E2%80%99%20with%20the%20caveat%20that%20%E2%80%98the%20obscenity%20has%20to%20be%20judged%20from%20the%20point%20of%20view%20of%20an%20average%20person%2C%20by%20applying%20contemporary%20community%20standards.%E2%80%99%20Both%20these%20tests%20for%20obscenity%20follow%20from%20the%20overbroad%20and%20subjective%20phrasing%20in%20the%20section%20itself%2C%20and%20depend%20entirely%20on%20personal%20and%20community%20morality%20to%20determine%20whether%20or%20not%20something%20is%20obscene.%20In%20recent%20years%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20ruled%20that%20it%20is%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F168671544%2F%5C%22%3Econstitutional%20morality%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20not%20personal%20morality%2C%20that%20should%20inform%20criminalisation.%20This%20is%20the%20only%20way%20to%20ensure%20that%20the%20standard%20of%20criminalisation%20is%20not%20solely%20based%20on%20whether%20the%20conduct%20in%20question%20offends%20one%E2%80%99s%20personal%20morality.%20Amending%20these%20provisions%20would%20have%20been%20a%20welcome%20step%20towards%20decolonising%20the%20law.%20Unfortunately%2C%20the%20BNS%20has%20retained%20the%20exact%20wording%20of%20the%20IPC%20provisions%20on%20obscenity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ECriminalisation%20of%20abortion%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnother%20remnant%20of%20moralism%20in%20our%20criminal%20laws%20is%20Section%20312%20of%20the%20IPC%2C%20which%20criminalises%20abortion.%20Under%20this%20provision%20any%20person%20who%20voluntarily%20causes%20a%20woman%20to%20miscarry%20is%20liable%20to%20be%20punished.%20This%20also%20includes%20a%20pregnant%20woman%20who%20chooses%20abortion.%20The%20only%20exception%20is%20if%20such%20miscarriage%20is%20caused%20in%20good%20faith%20to%20save%20the%20pregnant%20woman%E2%80%99s%20life.%20The%20Medical%20Termination%20of%20Pregnancy%20Act%2C%201971%20(%E2%80%98MTP%20Act%E2%80%99)%20introduces%20further%20exceptions%20to%20this%20provision%20by%20protecting%20doctors%20from%20criminal%20liability%2C%20if%20they%20perform%20abortions%20under%20specific%20conditions%20prescribed%20under%20the%20Act.%20While%20the%20MTP%20Act%20has%20liberalised%20access%20to%20abortions%2C%20it%20relies%20on%20creating%20exceptions%20to%20the%20norm%20of%20criminalising%20abortion%20procedures.%20The%20introduction%20of%20a%20rights-based%20framework%20on%20abortion%E2%80%94another%20missed%20opportunity%E2%80%94would%20have%20constituted%20a%20substantive%20step%20towards%20decolonisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBy%20not%20using%20this%20opportunity%20to%20alter%20the%20law%20on%20these%20issues%2C%20the%20new%20Codes%20have%20actually%20reinforced%20and%20legitimised%20the%20pre-existing%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20statutes.%20Besides%20the%20specific%20provisions%20mapped%20above%2C%20the%20strongest%20counter%20to%20the%20logic%20of%20decolonisation%20is%20arguably%20the%20lack%20of%20any%20meaningful%20reform%20in%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20laws.%20The%20colonial%20logic%20of%20the%20law%2C%20in%20large%20part%2C%20lay%20in%20its%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cambridge.org%2Fcore%2Fjournals%2Flaw-and-history-review%2Farticle%2Fabs%2Fcodification-and-the-rule-of-colonial-difference-criminal-procedure-in-british-india%2F6163423C0490CAE1B323CB97CC89E2F5%5C%22%3Edifferentiated%20application%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0across%20white%20and%20the%20%E2%80%98native%E2%80%99%20populations.%20Even%20among%20the%20%E2%80%98natives%E2%80%99%2C%20class%2C%20caste%20and%20social%20stature%20determined%20outcomes%20in%20criminal%20cases.%20This%20colonial%20mentality%20continues%20till%20today%2C%20as%20is%20evident%20from%20prison%20statistics%20revealing%20that%20the%20criminal%20legal%20apparatus%20has%20a%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fncrb.gov.in%2Fuploads%2Fnationalcrimerecordsbureau%2Fcustom%2Fpsiyearwise2022%2F1701613297PSI2022ason01122023.pdf%5C%22%3Edisparate%20impact%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0on%20oppressed%20castes%20and%20religious%20minorities.%20While%20the%20new%20criminal%20laws%20claim%20to%20place%20the%20citizen%20at%20the%20centre%20of%20the%20justice%20delivery%20process%2C%20there%20is%20absolutely%20no%20mention%20of%20undoing%20the%20discriminatory%20impact%20and%20enforcement%20of%20the%20laws.%20In%20fact%2C%20by%20strengthening%20the%20state%20in%20an%20increasingly%20unequal%20society%2C%20these%20gaps%20will%20only%20be%20widened.%20Moreover%2C%20given%20the%20reality%20of%20large%20portions%20of%20BNS%2C%20BNSS%20and%20BSA%20being%20reproduced%20verbatim%20from%20the%20IPC%2C%20CrPC%2C%20and%20the%20IEA%2C%20the%20opportunity%20for%20a%20meaningful%20overhaul%20of%20the%20injustices%20perpetrated%20by%20the%20criminal%20legal%20system%20has%20been%20lost.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2Fmrinal-satish%2F%5C%22%3EMrinal%20Satish%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20a%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20NLSIU%2C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Ffaculty%2Fpreeti-pratishruti-dash%2F%5C%22%3EPreeti%20Pratishruti%20Dash%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20Assistant%20Professor%20of%20Law%20at%20NLSIU%20and%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Fpeople%2Fanushka-pandey%2F%5C%22%3EAnushka%20Pandey%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0is%20a%20Research%20Associate%20at%20NLSIU.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nls.ac.in%2Fblog%2Fbharatiya-nyaya-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%2F%5C%22%3Eoriginally%20published%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%20blog.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617825000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11180259%2FUneven.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbharatiya-nyay-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20new%20Codes%20have%20actually%20reinforced%20and%20legitimised%20the%20pre-existing%20coloniality%20in%20our%20criminal%20statutes.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fbharatiya-nyay-sanhita-decolonising-or-reinforcing-colonial-ideas%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Coming%20soon%3A%20A%20smartwatch%20from%20the%20company%20which%20sued%20Apple%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706617415000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-107265315%2Cimgsize-882175.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fcoming-soon-a-smartwatch-from-the-company-which-sued-apple-over-watch%2Farticleshow%2F107265312.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Masimo%2C%20the%20company%20that%20sued%20Apple%20for%20patent%20infringement%2C%20is%20launching%20its%20Freedom%20smartwatch%20with%20blood%20oxygen%20monitoring.%20The%20device%2C%20previewed%20at%20CES%202024%2C%20aims%20to%20demonstrate%20the%20accuracy%20of%20Masimo's%20health-monitoring%20technology.%20Masimo's%20CEO%2C%20Joe%20Kiani%2C%20opposed%20Apple's%20emergency%20motion%20to%20stay%20enforcement%20of%20the%20import%20ban%20and%20criticized%20Apple's%20product%20performance.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20TECH%20DESK%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fgadgets-news%2Fcoming-soon-a-smartwatch-from-the-company-which-sued-apple-over-watch%2Farticleshow%2F107265312.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20Does%20'Integral%20Humanism'%20Really%20Mean%20to%20the%20BJP%3F%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30161148%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EOn%20the%20third%20page%20of%20its%20constitution%2C%20the%20BJP%20lays%20out%20its%20membership%20conditions%3A%20%E2%80%9CAny%20Indian%20citizen%20of%2018%20years%20or%20above%20who%20accepts%20Articles%20II%2C%20III%20and%20IV%20of%20the%20constitution%20shall%2C%20on%20making%20a%20written%20declaration%E2%80%A6%20become%20a%20member%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20BJP.%20What%20are%20these%20things%20that%20are%20important%20enough%20to%20make%20a%20written%20declaration%3F%20Article%20II%20of%20the%20BJP%20constitution%20concludes%20thus%3A%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20party%20shall%20bear%20true%20faith%20and%20allegiance%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India%20as%20by%20law%20established%20and%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20socialism%2C%20secularism%20and%20democracy%E2%80%9D.%20Article%20IV%20says%20the%20party%20commits%20itself%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9CGandhian%20approach%20to%20socio-economic%20issues%20leading%20to%20establishment%20of%20egalitarian%20society%20free%20from%20exploitation%E2%80%9D.%20It%20adds%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cparty%20stands%20for%20decentralisation%20of%20economic%20and%20political%20power%E2%80%9D.%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhere%20do%20these%20matters%20figure%20in%20the%20way%20the%20party%20actually%20conducts%20itself%3F%20This%20will%20be%20interesting%20to%20see%2C%20but%20that%E2%80%99s%20for%20another%20time.%20Article%20III%2C%20the%20subject%20of%20this%20column%2C%20is%20a%20single%20line%20which%20reads%20%E2%80%9CIntegral%20Humanism%20shall%20be%20the%20basic%20philosophy%20of%20the%20party%E2%80%9D.%20Integral%20Humanism%20is%20the%20subject%20of%20four%20lectures%20in%20Mumbai%20given%20by%20Deen%20Dayal%20Upadhyaya%20between%20April%2022%20and%2025%2C%201965.%20Upadhyaya%20held%20a%20BA%20degree%20and%20was%20a%20journalist%20at%20the%20RSS%E2%80%99s%20in-house%20Panchjanya.%20He%20was%20about%2050%20when%20he%20delivered%20these%20lectures%20and%20became%20president%20of%20the%20Jan%20Sangh%20(the%20BJP%E2%80%99s%20precursor)%20a%20couple%20of%20years%20after%20he%20delivered%20them.%20The%20following%20is%20a%20summary%20of%20the%20argument%20Upadhyaya%20presents%3A%3Cb%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20cause%20of%20the%20problems%20facing%20Bharat%20is%20a%20neglect%20of%20national%20identity.%20The%20nation%20is%20like%20an%20individual%20and%20becomes%20ill%20if%20its%20natural%20instincts%20are%20disregarded%20or%20suppressed.%20Seventeen%20years%20after%20Independence%2C%20India%20was%20undecided%20about%20the%20direction%20it%20would%20take%20towards%20development.%20Independence%20is%20meaningful%20only%20it%20is%20the%20instrument%20to%20express%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*The%20focus%20in%20India%20was%20on%20episodic%20problems%3A%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20political.%20This%20was%20because%20India%20adopted%20a%20Western%20way%20of%20looking%20at%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20political%20doctrines%20along%20with%20Western%20science.%20Westernisation%20was%20synonymous%20with%20progress%20for%20Indians.%20However%2C%20the%20West%20was%20unable%20to%20reconcile%20nationalism%2C%20democracy%20and%20socialism.%20These%20were%20essentially%20Western%20ideals%20and%20they%20were%20all%20in%20conflict%20with%20one%20another.%20These%20ideologies%20were%20not%20universal%20and%20not%20free%20from%20the%20limitations%20of%20the%20people%20and%20cultures%20which%20gave%20birth%20to%20these%20isms.%20Ayurveda%20said%20that%20we%20need%20to%20find%20local%20cures%20to%20local%20diseases.%20Could%20Bharatiya%20culture%20provide%20a%20solution%20for%20the%20world%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Dharma%20is%20given%20foremost%20place%20in%20Bharatiya%20culture.%20Dharma%20is%20the%20natural%20law%20that%20is%20eternal%20and%20universally%20applicable.%20Dharma%20is%20ethics%20teaching%20us%20not%20to%20lie%2C%20not%20to%20fight.%20When%20nature%20is%20directed%20according%20to%20the%20principles%20of%20dharma%2C%20there%20is%20culture%20and%20civilisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Dharma%20is%20higher%20than%20the%20executive%2C%20legislative%20and%20judiciary.%20It%20is%20also%20higher%20than%20the%20people.%20If%20out%20of%20450%20million%20Indians%2C%20all%20except%20one%20voted%20for%20something%2C%20it%20would%20still%20be%20wrong%20if%20it%20was%20against%20dharma.%20The%20people%20have%20no%20right%20to%20act%20against%20dharma.%20The%20words%20%E2%80%9Csecularism%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdharmnirpeksh%E2%80%9D%20(the%20Hindi%20phrase%20for%20secularism%20meaning%20%E2%80%9Cthat%20which%20is%20not%20dependent%20on%20dharma%E2%80%9D)%20in%20the%20Constitution%20are%20wrong%20and%20bad%20because%20dharma%20is%20a%20necessary%20condition%20for%20the%20State.%20That%20which%20is%20not%20based%20on%20dharma%20is%20unacceptable%2C%20and%20therefore%20secularism%20was%20fatally%20flawed.%20National%20unity%20is%20India%E2%80%99s%20dharma%3B%20so%20diversity%20was%20problematic.%20For%20this%20reason%2C%20India%E2%80%99s%20Constitution%20needs%20to%20be%20changed%20from%20federal%20to%20unitary%2C%20with%20no%20legislative%20powers%20for%20the%20states%2C%20only%20for%20the%20Centre.%20Conflict%20between%20individuals%20and%20institutions%20of%20society%20is%20a%20sign%20of%20decadence%20and%20perversion.%20The%20West%20was%20wrong%20to%20see%20the%20adversarial%20relationship%20between%20the%20individual%20and%20the%20State%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20progress.%20The%20individual%20was%20made%20up%20of%20body%2C%20mind%2C%20intelligence%20and%20soul.%20A%20human%20being%20is%20born%20with%20a%20soul.%3Cb%3E%3C%2Fb%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPersonality%2C%20soul%20and%20character%20are%20different%20from%20one%20another.%20The%20person%E2%80%99s%20soul%20is%20unaffected%20by%20personal%20history.%20Similarly%2C%20national%20culture%20is%20continuously%20modified%20by%20history.%20Culture%20includes%20all%20things%20held%20as%20good%20and%20commendable%2C%20but%20they%20do%20not%20affect%20%E2%80%9Cchiti%E2%80%9D%2C%20the%20national%20soul.%20India%E2%80%99s%20national%20soul%20is%20fundamental%20and%20central.%20Chiti%20determines%20the%20direction%20of%20cultural%20advance.%20It%20filters%20out%20what%20is%20to%20be%20excluded%20from%20culture.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E*Societies%20are%20animate%20and%20a%20society%20has%20a%20body%2C%20mind%2C%20intellect%20and%20soul.%20Some%20Westerners%20were%20beginning%20to%20accept%20this%20truth.%20One%20of%20them%2C%20William%20McDougall%2C%20said%20that%20a%20group%20had%20a%20mind%20and%20a%20psychology%2C%20its%20own%20methods%20of%20thinking%20and%20action%20just%20as%20an%20individual%20did.%20Societies%20have%20an%20inborn%20nature%20that%E2%80%99s%20not%20based%20on%20its%20history.%20Events%20don%E2%80%99t%20affect%20it.%20This%20group%20nature%20is%20like%20the%20soul%20in%20individuals%2C%20also%20unaffected%20by%20history.%20This%20group%20mentality%20is%20like%20mob%20mentality%20but%20developed%20over%20a%20longer%20period.%20The%20nation%20needs%20both%20an%20ideal%20and%20a%20motherland%20and%20only%20then%20is%20it%20a%20nation.%20The%20State%20exists%20to%20protect%20this%20nation%2C%20which%20has%20an%20ideal%20and%20a%20motherland.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20the%20message%20of%20the%20four%20lectures.%20It%20is%20not%20easy%20to%20figure%20out%20what%20the%20meaning%20of%20it%20all%20is.%20What%2C%20for%20instance%2C%20is%20the%20difference%20between%20mind%20and%20intelligence%3F%20What%20is%20a%20soul%3F%20How%20are%20these%20three%20things%20separate%20from%20a%20body%3F%20What%20does%20the%20sentence%20that%20%E2%80%9Cpersonality%2C%20soul%20and%20character%20are%20all%20distinct%20from%20one%20another%E2%80%9D%20really%20mean%3F%20And%20what%20is%20the%20role%20of%20a%20political%20party%20and%20of%20government%20in%20any%20of%20this%3F%20The%20national%20soul%2C%20%E2%80%9Cchiti%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20group%20mind%20are%20not%20scientific%20phenomena%20and%20the%20works%20of%20William%20McDougall%20are%20not%20science%20(he%20thought%2C%20like%20Upadhyaya%20did%2C%20that%20the%20mind%20influenced%20evolution).%20One%20wonders%20how%20many%20BJP%20members%20who%20sign%20written%20declarations%20saying%20they%20accept%20Integral%20Humanism%20as%20their%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20philosophy%E2%80%9D%20actually%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20that%20they%20have%20accepted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EAakar%20Patel%20is%20an%20author%20and%20columnist.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706616039000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30161148%2F406110211_773446158163006_4756603232278021214_n.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-does-integral-humanism-really-mean-to-the-bjp%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22One%20wonders%20how%20many%20BJP%20members%20who%20sign%20written%20declarations%20saying%20they%20accept%20Integral%20Humanism%20as%20their%20%E2%80%9Cbasic%20philosophy%E2%80%9D%20actually%20understand%20what%20it%20is%20that%20they%20have%20accepted.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fwhat-does-integral-humanism-really-mean-to-the-bjp%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Flashpoints%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20Gaza%2C%20Yemen%20and%20Taiwan%20Point%20to%20a%20Global%20War%20in%20the%20Making%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20winning%20the%202020%20election%20on%20a%20platform%20of%20ending%20America%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cforever%20wars%E2%80%9D%2C%20and%20withdrawing%20from%20Afghanistan%20in%202021%2C%20Joseph%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20is%20a%20war%20presidency.%20And%20the%20United%20States%20remains%20a%20world%20power%20at%20the%20core%20of%20which%20is%20a%20foreign%20policy%20establishment%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-david-vine-the-united-states-of-war%5C%22%3Ewedded%20to%20its%20war%20machine%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20war%20mentality%20and%20machine%20is%20the%20bedrock%20of%20Washington%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20to%20sustain%20its%20primacy%20in%20global%20affairs%2C%20as%20its%20global%20positions%20come%20under%20increasing%20pressure%20from%20emerging%20midd