0in%20January%202025%20is%20in%20jeopardy%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWars%20abroad%2C%20political%20violence%20at%20home%3A%20Empires%20usually%20decay%20from%20within%20but%20in%20the%20age%20of%20globalisation%20and%20digitisation%2C%20the%20repercussions%20and%20reverberations%20would%20be%20worldwide.%20In%20such%20conditions%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fbooks%2Fbook-review-america-militarism%5C%22%3Efear%3C%2Fa%3E%20becomes%20a%20major%20force%20to%20mobilise%20opinion%20behind%20warfare.%20But%20the%20post-1945%20American%20century%20was%20born%20%E2%80%9Cscaring%20hell%E2%80%9D%20out%20of%20the%20American%20people.%20And%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmuse.jhu.edu%2Farticle%2F433950%2Fsummary%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9Cpermanent%20war%20for%20permanent%20peace%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0became%20the%20emblem%20of%20the%20topsy-turvy%20world%20of%20the%20US%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EIsrael-Gaza%20war%20spiralling%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20most%20recent%20phase%20of%20the%20unfolding%20of%20international%20war%20and%20violence%20is%20fuelled%20largely%20by%20America%E2%80%99s%20constant%20and%20generous%20military%2C%20financial%2C%20and%20diplomatic%20support%20to%20Tel%20Aviv.%20Israel%20has%20built%20and%20consolidated%20an%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hrw.org%2Fnews%2F2021%2F07%2F19%2Fisraeli-apartheid-threshold-crossed%5C%22%3Eapartheid%20system%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20home%2C%20and%20a%20regime%20that%20indulges%20in%20what%20is%20increasingly%20viewed%20across%20the%20world%20(outside%20the%20core%20states%20of%20the%20liberal%20rules-based%20international%20order)%20as%20genocide%20with%20impunity%20in%20Gaza.%20Indeed%2C%20South%20Africa%20has%20taken%20the%20case%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fforeignpolicy.com%2F2024%2F01%2F17%2Fisrael-gaza-icj-genocide-south-africa-namibia-bangladesh-global-south%2F%5C%22%3EInternational%20Court%20of%20Justice%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20received%20support%20from%20several%20other%20states.%20Israel%20is%20also%20launching%20military%20strikes%20against%20Lebanon%20and%20Syria%20and%20uses%20Sunni%20terrorists%20based%20in%20Iraq%2C%20Syria%2C%20and%20Pakistan%20against%20Iran.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIsrael%20and%20the%20United%20States%20are%20not%20alone%C2%A0in%20supporting%20radical%20groups%20in%20pursuance%20of%20their%20foreign%20and%20security%20policies.%20Iran%20supports%20or%20is%20partnered%20with%20Hezbollah%20in%20Lebanon%20and%20Houthis%20in%20Yemen.%20But%20Tehran%E2%80%99s%20reach%20and%20range%20to%20mobilise%20military%20conflict%20on%C2%A0a%20global%20scale%20pales%20in%20comparison%20with%20American%20capability%20to%20provoke%20and%20sustain%20hostilities%20across%20geographies.%20Other%20states%20can%20launch%20wars%3B%20only%20the%20US%20empire%20can%20extract%20strategic%20mileage%20and%20commercial%20benefits%20from%20wars.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11160252%2FGA6xi9-WoAEKSsS.jpeg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11160252%2FGA6xi9-WoAEKSsS.jpeg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11160252%2FGA6xi9-WoAEKSsS-300x163.jpeg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F11160252%2FGA6xi9-WoAEKSsS-1024x555.jpeg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688654%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22650%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EA%20bombed%20locality%20in%20Gaza.%20Photo%3A%20Ashfaq%20Amra%2FUNRWA%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica%E2%80%99s%20war%20machine%20is%20ravenous%2C%20hence%20its%20readiness%20to%20participate%20in%20every%20big%20and%20small%20war%20stems%20from%20its%20need%20to%20justify%20its%20humongous%20annual%20military%20budget%20of%20over%20%24800%20billion.%20Its%20military-industrial%20complex%20needs%20to%20sell%20lethal%20products%20and%20carry%20out%20live%20trials%20of%20its%20newly%20designed%20weapons.%20But%20even%20these%20factors%20are%20trumped%20by%20the%20US%20foreign%20policy%20establishment%E2%80%99s%20irrational%2C%20but%20growing%2C%20insecurities%20due%20to%20the%20ensuing%20imperial%20%E2%80%98decline%E2%80%99%20amid%20the%20rise%20of%20the%20Eurasian%20continent%20as%20a%20challenge%20to%20its%20sea%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ELand%20power%20versus%20sea%20power%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20maritime%20world%20%E2%80%93%20dominated%20first%20by%20Britain%E2%80%99s%20Royal%20Navy%20that%20%E2%80%9Cruled%20the%20waves%E2%80%9D%20(and%20%E2%80%9Cwaived%20the%20rules%E2%80%9D)%2C%20and%20latterly%20by%20US%20naval%20forces%20%E2%80%93%20fears%20being%20outflanked%20by%20the%20combined%20strength%20of%20Germany%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20China%20forming%20an%20alliance%20across%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%20As%20in%20the%20past%2C%20so%20it%20is%20today%3A%20maritime%20powers%20resort%20to%20wars%20to%20break%20emerging%20connectivities%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20vision%20of%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapps.dtic.mil%2Fsti%2Fcitations%2FADA138432%5C%22%3EBerlin-Baghdad%20railway%3C%2Fa%3E%20before%20World%20War%20I%2C%20or%20any%20Sino-Russian-Iranian%20bloc%20across%20Eurasia.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnglo-American%20maritime%20hegemony%20and%20power%20over%20the%20rhythms%20of%20global%20commerce%20are%20under%20stress.%20There%20is%20a%20growing%20clamour%20to%20re-negotiate%20and%20re-envision%20global%20order%20with%20the%20Eurasian%20region%20at%20its%20center%2C%20or%20at%20least%20more%20central%20than%20it%20has%20historically%20been.%20The%20patterns%20of%20competition%2C%20conflict%2C%20and%C2%A0cooperation%20are%20playing%20out%20with%20regard%20to%20connectivity%2C%20trade%2C%20supply%20routes%2C%20and%20resources%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20revival%20of%20rail%20technology.%20The%20old%20Silk%20Road%20replaced%20by%20the%20lightning%20speed%20of%20the%20iron%20and%20steel%20of%20the%20high-speed%20freight%20train.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGeographically%2C%20Eurasia%20is%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20most%20expansive%20region%20that%20forms%20a%20land%20bridge%20that%20borders%20Europe%2C%20the%20Asia-Pacific%2C%20West%20Asia%2C%20and%20South%20Asia.%20The%20Eurasian%20Land%20Bridge%20has%20the%20potential%20to%20undermine%20(or%20complement)%20existing%20seaborne%20supply%20lines%20by%20establishing%20a%20direct%20link%20between%20the%20Atlantic%20and%20Pacific.%20Maintaining%20a%20balance%20of%20power%20in%20Eurasia%20by%20splitting%20the%20continent%20while%20forming%20a%20consortium%20of%20major%20navies%20has%20been%20the%20mainstay%20of%20the%C2%A0strategy%20of%20maritime%20powers%20since%20World%20War%201.%20Prior%20to%20the%20start%20of%20the%20Great%20War%2C%C2%A0Britain%20entered%20into%20a%20naval%20alliance%20with%20America%20and%20the%20Triple%20Entente%20with%20Russia%20and%20France%20to%20keep%20Germany%20isolated.%20The%20US%20backed%20%C2%A0Britain%2C%20the%20declining%20maritime%20power%2C%C2%A0rather%20thang%C2%A0Germany%2C%20the%20emerging%20continental%20power.%20The%20Anglo-Americans%20wanted%20to%20preserve%20the%20primacy%20of%20oceans%20in%20the%20conduct%20of%20global%20affairs.%20The%20strategy%20of%20isolating%20Germany%20and%20preventing%20the%20Russo-German%20alliance%20from%20dominating%20Eurasia%20continued%20in%20the%20Second%20World%20War.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30160532%2FDanzig_Police_at_Polish_Border_1939-09-01.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30160532%2FDanzig_Police_at_Polish_Border_1939-09-01.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30160532%2FDanzig_Police_at_Polish_Border_1939-09-01-300x207.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30160532%2FDanzig_Police_at_Polish_Border_1939-09-01-1024x705.jpg%201024w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-694929%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22826%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3ESoldiers%20of%20the%20German%20Wehrmacht%20tearing%20down%20the%20border%20crossing%20into%20Poland%2C%201%20September%201939.%20Photo%3A%20Wikimedia%20Commons%2FHans%20S%C3%B6nnke%2FPublic%20Domain.%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWith%20postwar%20Germany%20under%20America%E2%80%99s%20thumb%2C%20Anglo-American%20strategy%20focused%20on%20splitting%20China%C2%A0and%20the%20Soviet%20Union.%20On%20the%C2%A0one%20hand%2C%20Britain%20wooed%20Beijing%20and%2C%20on%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20America%20applied%20pressure%20to%20it%2C%20in%20the%201950s.%20This%20carrot-and-stick%20policy%20changed%20in%20the%20late%201960s%20when%20America%20chased%20China%20unabashedly%2C%20culminating%20in%20the%20formal%20Sino-Soviet%20split.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnglo-American%20encouragement%20to%20Ukraine%20to%20take%20on%20Russia%E2%80%99s%20war%20machine%2C%20however%2C%20has%20only%20served%20to%20further%20cement%20Sino-US%20strategic%20relations.%20The%20current%20US%20strategy%20under%20Biden%20differs%20from%20that%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthediplomat.com%2F2017%2F02%2Fwhy-trump-cant-break-russia-away-from-china%2F%5C%22%3EPresident%20Trump%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%93%20which%20despite%20the%20latter%E2%80%99s%20crazy%20rhetoric%2C%20followed%20the%20more%20traditional%20divide-and-rule%20strategy%20by%20cosying%20up%20to%20Russia%20while%20applying%20extreme%20pressure%20on%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EHalford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20geopolitics%20lives%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EConsequently%2C%20Biden%E2%80%99s%20strategy%20has%20merely%20served%20to%20further%20cement%20Sino-Russian%20cooperation%2C%20and%20has%20been%20instrumental%20in%20reinvigorating%20the%20Eurasian%20dream%20by%20exploiting%20the%20latest%20developments%20in%20railroad%20technology.%20They%20are%20now%20practically%20realising%20British%20geopolitical%20theorist%20Halford%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%2C%20in%201904%2C%20that%20the%20inner%20area%20of%20Eurasia%2C%20impenetrable%20by%20sea%20power%2C%20would%20become%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.wikipedia.org%2Fwiki%2FThe_Geographical_Pivot_of_History%5C%22%3E%E2%80%9CPivot%20Area%E2%80%9D%20of%20world%20politics%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Mackinder%E2%80%99s%20prediction%20about%20the%20relative%20decline%20of%20maritime%20power%20due%20to%20the%20superiority%20of%20rail%20over%20ships%20in%20terms%20of%20speed%20and%20penetration%20is%20no%20longer%20far-fetched.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELook%20at%20the%20numbers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fglobalaffairs.org%2Fresearch%2Freport%2Feurasias-freight-infrastructure-vs-russias-war-ukraine%5C%22%3EOnly%2017%20freight%20trains%20%3C%2Fa%3Eran%20from%20China%20to%20Europe%20in%202011.%20Today%20more%20than%2060%2C000%20trains%20cumulatively%20ply%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass%20and%20its%20maritime%20margins.%20Current%20advances%20in%20rail%20technology%20and%20online%20trade%20trends%20that%20demand%20reduced%20delivery%20time%C2%A0%20are%20indicative%20of%20the%20growing%20salience%20of%20transcontinental%20rail%20connectivity%20in%20conduct%20of%20international%20trade.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEurasian%20landmass%20connectivity%20%E2%80%93%20railway%20corridor%20passing%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20Russia%2C%20and%20Belarus%20%E2%80%93%20impacts%20the%20overall%20economic%20effects%20of%20American%20naval%20capabilities%20to%20cut%20off%20Chinese%20trade%20and%20supply%20routes%20at%20Malacca%20straits.%C2%A0%20The%20Chinese%20answer%20to%20its%20%E2%80%9C%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fgjia.georgetown.edu%2F2023%2F03%2F22%2Fchinas-economic-security-challenge-difficulties-overcoming-the-malacca-dilemma%2F%5C%22%3EMalacca%20Dilemma%E2%80%9D%20%E2%80%93%20the%20threat%20of%20a%20naval%20blockade%20of%20vital%20Chinese%20sea%20lines%20of%20communication%20in%20the%20Indian%20Ocean%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20has%20been%20the%20carving%20out%20of%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20to%20the%20West%2C%20all%20the%20way%20to%20Europe.%20However%2C%20the%20Chinese%20alternative%20trade%20routes%20are%20dependent%20on%20Russian%20cooperation.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2FCEFT%5C%22%3EThe%20China-Europe%20Freight%20Train%20(CEFT)%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20heavily%20dependent%20on%20Russia%20%C2%A0%E2%80%9Cas%20both%20the%20most%20important%20terminus%20and%20through-corridor%20accounting%20for%2037%25%20of%20all%20CEFTs%20through%202021%2C%20leading%20Germany%20at%2024.3%25%20and%20Poland%20at%2023.4%25.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAmerica%20did%20not%20tolerate%20Sino-Soviet%20unity%20in%20the%20Cold%20War%2C%20and%20it%20will%20not%20do%20so%20now.%20The%20war%20in%20Europe%20has%20disrupted%20the%20development%20of%20these%20connectivity%20projects%20due%20to%20sanctions%20imposed%20on%20Russia%2C%20thereby%20adversely%20impacting%C2%A0China%E2%80%99s%20long-term%20interests%20in%20the%20Eurasian%20region.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20many%20companies%20operating%20rail%20freight%20between%20China%20and%20the%20EU%20are%20avoiding%20transit%20through%20Russia%2C%20resulting%20in%20greater%20use%20of%20the%20Middle%20Corridor%20(the%20Trans-Caspian%20International%20Transport%20Route)%E2%80%94from%20Southeast%20Asia%20and%20China%20through%20Kazakhstan%2C%20the%20Caspian%20Sea%2C%20Azerbaijan%2C%20and%20Georgia%E2%80%94as%20an%20alternative%20route%2C%20causing%20longer%20journeys%20and%20increased%20costs.%20The%20West%20is%20likely%20to%20support%20Ukraine%E2%80%99s%20fight%20against%20Russia%20until%2C%20of%20course%2C%20the%20latter%20is%20economically%20and%20militarily%20exhausted%20and%20willing%20to%20reassess%20its%20look-east%20policy%20and%C2%A0relationship%20with%20China.%20This%20looks%20a%20long%20way%20off%2C%20and%20promises%20continuation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforever%20wars%E2%80%9D%20dispensation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilarly%2C%20in%20the%20recent%20Pakistan-Iran%20conflict%2C%20what%20has%20come%20to%20light%20is%20the%20involvement%20of%20Balochistan%2C%20with%20the%20Gwadar%20port%20located%20close%20to%20the%20Gulf%20of%20Oman%2C%20an%20important%20link%20in%20the%20new%20silk%20road%20envisaged%20by%20China.%20Damascus%E2%80%94the%20traditional%20terminus%20node%20of%20the%20ancient%20Silk%20Road%E2%80%94is%20also%20embroiled%20in%20a%20conflict%20situation%20and%20is%20a%20pariah%20state%20in%20the%20western%20geopolitical%20equation.%20In%202022%2C%20there%20were%20clashes%20on%20the%20Tajikistan-Kyrgyzstan%20border.%20In%20the%20beginning%20of%202022%2C%20Kazakistan%20witnessed%20violent%20protests%20against%20President%20Kassym-Jomart%20Tokayev%E2%80%99s%20rule.%20The%20Armenia-Azerbaijan%20hostilities%20over%20the%20disputed%20Nagorno-Karabakh%20republic%20provide%20America%20with%20an%20opportunity%20to%20meddle%20in%20Central%20Asia%20to%20put%20pressure%20on%20the%20China-Russia%20alliance.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2020th%20century%2C%20Germany%E2%80%99s%20plans%20to%20build%20the%20Berlin-Baghdad%20rail%20link%20became%20one%20of%20the%20most%20important%20reasons%20for%20World%20War%20I%2C%20as%20they%20threatened%20the%20British-controlled%20sea%20lanes%20of%20communication%20passing%20through%20the%20Suez%20Canal.%20It%20was%20seen%20as%20part%20of%20an%20inter-imperial%20assault%20on%20the%20British%20empire.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20home%2C%20the%20major%20colonial%20powers%20faced%20growing%20political%20discontent%2C%20economic%20inequality%2C%20mass%20immiseration%2C%20and%20the%20emergence%20of%20powerful%20trade%20union%2C%20worker%2C%20and%20socialist%20movements%20against%20capitalism%20and%20empire.%20A%20world%20war%20resulted.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20dawn%20of%20the%2021%20century%2C%20we%20live%20in%20a%20world%20best%20described%20by%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheroadsinitiative.org%2Fpoly-crisis-or-organic-crisis-the-crisis-of-the-united-states-and-the-us-led-world-order%2F%5C%22%3Ecrisis%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20whether%20called%20%E2%80%9Cpoly%E2%80%9D%2C%20%E2%80%9Cperma%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20organic.%20At%20home%20in%20so%20many%20countries%20across%20the%20world%2C%20we%20see%20popular%20resistance%20to%20elite%20rule%2C%20crises%20of%20legitimacy%20and%20authority%2C%20increasing%20political%20polarisation%20and%20violence%2C%20the%20politics%20of%20right-wing%20racist%2C%20and%20communal%20divide%20and%20rule.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGlobally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20struggle%20for%20hegemony%20and%20empire%20is%20increasingly%20breaking%20out%20into%20violence.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%20Flashpoints%20from%20Ukraine%20to%20Gaza%20to%20Yemen%20to%20Taiwan%20%E2%80%93%20disciplinary%20military%20confrontations%20for%20containment%20on%20the%20borders%20of%20Eurasia%20and%20its%20core%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EDr%20Atul%20Bhardwaj%20is%20an%20honorary%20research%20fellow%20in%20the%20department%20of%20international%20politics%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London.%20He%20is%20the%20author%20of%20%3C%2Fem%3EIndia-America%20Relations%20(1942-62)%3A%20Rooted%20in%20the%20Liberal%20International%20Order%20%3Cem%3E(Routledge%2C%202018)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fauthor%2Fiparmar%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EInderjeet%20Parmar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E%20is%20a%20professor%20of%20international%20politics%20and%20associate%20dean%20of%20research%20in%20the%20School%20of%20Policy%20and%20Global%20Affairs%20at%20City%2C%20University%20of%20London%2C%20a%20fellow%20of%20the%20Academy%20of%20Social%20Sciences%2C%20and%20a%20columnist%20at%20%3C%2Fem%3EThe%20Wire%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20an%20International%20Fellow%20at%20the%20ROADS%20Initiative%20think%20tank%2C%20Islamabad%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20%3Cem%3Eand%20author%20of%20several%20books%20including%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EFoundations%20of%20the%20American%20Century%3Cem%3E.%20He%20is%20currently%20writing%20a%20book%20on%20the%20history%2C%20politics%2C%20and%20powers%20of%20the%20US%20Foreign%20Policy%20Establishment.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706614216000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F20120344%2FAnti-terrorist_operation_in_eastern_Ukraine_War_Ukraine_26894689722.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Globally%2C%20the%20geopolitical%20and%20geoeconomic%20cracks%20in%20a%20system%20of%20complex%20interdependence%20are%20evolving%20into%20schisms.%20The%20world%20appears%20to%20be%20heading%20towards%20another%20major%20war%20on%20a%20global%20scale%20over%20supply%20lines%2C%20alternative%20trade%20routes%2C%20control%20of%20the%20seas%2C%20and%20the%20Eurasian%20landmass.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fflashpoints-in-ukraine-gaza-yemen-and-taiwan-point-to-a-global-war-in-the-making%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20pics%3A%20Connection%20between