227.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Ladakh%3A%20Local%20Herders%20Clash%20With%20Chinese%20Soldiers%20Over%20Access%20to%20Grazing%20Land%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30163202%2FIMG_5078.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20Tension%20continues%20to%20prevail%20in%20a%20remote%20border%20region%20in%20Ladakh%20after%20local%20herders%20reportedly%20pelted%20stones%20at%20a%20Chinese%20Army%20patrolling%20unit%20earlier%20this%20month%2C%20after%20they%20were%20allegedly%20denied%20access%20to%20their%20traditional%20grazing%20lands.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELocals%20and%20officials%20said%20that%20the%20clash%20took%20place%20on%20January%202%20in%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Nyoma%20village%20in%20Chushul%20Valley%20of%20Ladakh%2C%20which%20borders%20the%20Tibet%20region%20controlled%20by%20China.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20group%20of%20local%20herders%20were%20intercepted%20at%20Patrolling%20Point%2035%2C%2036%20and%2037%20in%20Dungti%20village%20of%20Nyoma%20along%20the%20border%20with%20China%20by%20at%20least%20a%20dozen%20visibly%20unarmed%20soldiers%20of%20People%E2%80%99s%20Liberation%20Army%20(PLA)%2C%20who%20were%20also%20accompanied%20by%20three%20armoured%20vehicles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20video%20clip%20of%20the%20clash%2C%20which%20has%20been%20verified%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20was%20shared%20by%20Kunsang%20Namjal%2C%20an%20Instagram%20user%2C%20which%20shows%20a%20herder%20using%20a%20rope%20as%20a%20sling%20to%20pelt%20stones%20at%20the%20incoming%20PLA%20vehicles%2C%20while%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20and%20other%20herders%20purportedly%20ask%20him%20to%20calm%20down.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWhy%20have%20you%20come%20here%3F%20Why%20have%20you%20brought%20your%20vehicles%20here%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20herder%20can%20be%20seen%20shouting%20at%20a%20PLA%20soldier%20in%20Tibetan%20language%2C%20as%20the%20siren%20of%20one%20of%20the%20PLA%20armoured%20vehicles%20blares%20in%20the%20background.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20continued%3A%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20our%20ancestral%20land.%20We%20graze%20our%20livestock%20here.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%209-minute%2C%2050-second%20video%20shows%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20and%20the%20herders%20getting%20into%20a%20heated%20argument%20as%20they%20come%20face%20to%20face.%20The%20video%20shows%20one%20batch%20of%20Chinese%20soldiers%2C%20led%20by%20an%20armoured%20vehicle%2C%20pushing%20the%20herders%20and%20their%20livestock%20back.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20PLA%20soldier%20can%20also%20be%20seen%20blocking%20the%20camera%20lens%20of%20the%20herder%2C%20who%20is%20shooting%20the%20incident%2C%20even%20as%20his%20fellow%20soldiers%20around%20him%20continue%20to%20film%20the%20incident%20while%20waving%20at%20the%20herders%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20a%20visibly-agitated%20herder%2C%20who%20breaks%20from%20the%20scene%2C%20pulls%20out%20a%20sling%20from%20beneath%20his%20coat%2C%20puts%20a%20stone%20in%20it%20and%20swings%20it%20at%20the%20incoming%20armoured%20vehicle%2C%20which%20visibly%20escaped%20the%20hit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20has%20reached%20out%20to%20Deputy%20Commissioner%20Leh%20Santosh%20Sukhadeva%20and%20SSP%20Leh%20for%20their%20comment%20about%20the%20development.%20This%20article%20will%20be%20updated%20when%20they%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EChushul%20Councillor%20Konchok%20Stanzin%2C%20who%20posted%20the%20video%20on%20X%2C%20formerly%20Twitter%2C%20said%20that%20nomads%20put%20up%20a%20brave%20face%20when%20the%20PLA%20soldiers%20stopped%20their%20livestock%20from%20grazing.%20%E2%80%9CLivelihoods%20of%20locals%20have%20been%20taken%20away%20in%20the%20name%20of%20buffer%20zones%20and%20patrolling%20points.%20Our%20nomads%20are%20struggling%20for%20their%20land%2C%E2%80%9D%20Stanzin%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20the%20clash%2C%20the%20herders%20were%20forced%20to%20move%20out%20of%20the%20area%2C%20sparking%20anger%20in%20the%20nomadic%20community%20who%20depend%20on%20the%20pastures%20in%20the%20highlands%20of%20Ladakh%20for%20their%20survival.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20is%20not%20the%20first%20time%20Chinese%20soldiers%20have%20turned%20away%20nomads%20from%20their%20traditional%20lands%20in%20Ladakh.%20In%20the%20past%2C%20there%20have%20been%20several%20reports%20of%20incursion%20by%20China%20with%20Indian%20patrols%20also%20reportedly%20losing%20access%20to%20the%20strategic%20Depsang%20Plains%2C%20Demchok%20and%20other%20areas%20in%20eastern%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20opposition%20led%20by%20the%20Congress%20has%20accused%20the%20Narendra%20Modi%20government%20of%20covering%20up%20%E2%80%9Cterritorial%20setbacks%E2%80%9D%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20while%20the%20Union%20government%20has%20denied%20the%20charges%20as%20%E2%80%9Cpolitically%20motivated%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELast%20year%2C%20a%20landmark%20built%20by%20the%20Indian%20Army%20at%20the%20site%20of%20the%20Rezang%20La%20battle%20of%20the%201962%20Sino-India%20conflict%20in%20Ladakh%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Frezang-la-battle-landmark-removed-as-part-of-disengagement-councillor-says%5C%22%3Ewas%20dismantled%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20part%20of%20the%20disengagement%20process%20with%20China%2C%20prompting%20anger%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDiplomatic%20and%20military%20level%20talks%20on%20the%20border%20dispute%20between%20the%20two%20countries%20have%20failed%20to%20make%20any%20significant%20headway%20in%20recent%20years%20as%20relations%20between%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20giants%20has%20soured%20over%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20growing%20camaraderie%20with%20Washington.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20Galwan%20Valley%20clashes%20which%20brought%20the%20two%20South%20Asian%20giants%20on%20the%20brink%20of%20a%20full-blown%20war%20in%202020-2021%2C%20traditional%20grazing%20land%20has%20turned%20into%20a%20buffer%20zone%20at%20many%20places%20in%20Ladakh%2C%20increasing%20the%20difficulties%20of%20nomadic%20herders.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20Stimson%20Centre%2C%20a%20Washington-based%20online%20policy%20platform%2C%20the%20lack%20of%20a%20clear%20demarcation%20of%20the%20border%20between%20India%20and%20China%20and%20continuing%20Chinese%20incursions%20in%20Chushul%2C%20Chumur%2C%20Dungti%2C%20Phobrang%2C%20and%20Demchok%20has%20adversely%20affected%20the%20life%20of%20Changpas%2C%20a%20nomadic%20community%20which%20lives%20along%20the%20Line%20of%20Actual%20Control%20in%20Ladakh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20conflict%20and%20the%20lack%20of%20development%20in%20border%20villages%20have%20forced%20many%20to%20flee%20to%20the%20town%20of%20Leh%20and%20thus%20the%20looming%20danger%20of%20mass%20migration%20from%20the%20border%20villages%20requires%20timely%20intervention%20by%20the%20Indian%20government%20and%20an%20inclusive%20Ladakh%20policy%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20centre%20noted%20in%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fsouthasianvoices.org%2Fassessing-the-human-impact-of-the-india-china-border-dispute%2F%5C%22%3Ereport%20in%20its%C2%A0%3Cem%3ESouth%20Asian%20Voices%3C%2Fem%3E%C2%A0journal%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706612848000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F30163202%2FIMG_5078.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fladakh-local-herders-clash-with-chinese-solders-over-access-to-grazing-land%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Locals%20and%20officials%20said%20that%20the%20clash%20took%20place%20on%20January%202%20in%20the%20Kakjung%20area%20of%20Nyoma%20village%20in%20Chushul%20Valley%2C%20Ladakh%2C%20which%20borders%20the%20Tibet%20region.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A26%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fsecurity%2Fladakh-local-herders-clash-with-chinese-solders-over-access-to-grazing-land%22%2C%22cdnA