ons%2C%20more%20than%20450%20writers%2C%20intellectuals%2C%20artists%2C%20journalists%20and%20eminent%20citizens%20of%20Assam%20have%20made%20a%20public%20appeal%20today%20to%20uphold%20Gandhian%20principles%20on%20the%20martyrdom%20anniversary%20of%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20father.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20day%20in%201948%2C%20Mahatma%20Gandhi%20was%20assassinated%20by%20a%20Hindu%20fanatic%20during%20a%20prayer%20meeting%20in%20Delhi.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20public%20appeal%20underlined%20that%20Gandhi%20was%20a%20deeply%20religious%20person%20and%20a%20devout%20Hindu.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20for%20him%20the%20essence%20of%20religion%20was%20justice.%20He%20never%20compromised%20with%20the%20principles%20of%20truth%2C%20nonviolence%20and%20justice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHere%20is%20the%20full%20appeal%20signed%20by%20a%20cross%20section%20of%20people%20in%20the%20northeastern%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELet%20us%20uphold%20the%20principles%20of%20Gandhism.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EGandhiji%20was%20the%20tallest%20leader%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement.%20Finally%2C%20after%20years%20of%20struggle%2C%20the%20British%20had%20to%20leave%20the%20country%20and%20we%20gained%20our%20freedom.%20But%2C%20freedom%20came%20at%20the%20cost%20of%20partition%20of%20the%20country.%20The%20moment%20of%20the%20celebration%20of%20freedom%20was%20marred%20by%20widespread%20communal%20violence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAt%20(During)%20that%20crisis%2C%20when%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20freedom%20movement%20were%20hoisting%20the%20Indian%20flag%20in%20Delhi%2C%20Gandhiji%20was%20in%20remote%20villages%20dousing%20communal%20violence%20and%20bringing%20solace%20to%20the%20victims%20of%20the%20riots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20trying%20to%20bring%20unity%20among%20the%20Hindus%20and%20Muslims%20Gandhiji%20was%20assassinated%20by%20a%20Nathuram%20Godse%2C%20a%20Hindu%20fanatic%20with%20known%20links%20to%20rabid%20Hindu%20nationalist%20organisations%20on%2030%20January%201948%20at%20Bi