icial%20state%20secrets%2C%20his%20party%20said%20today%2C%20January%2030.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFormer%20prime%20minister%20Imran%20Khan%20and%20PTI%20(Pakistan%20Tehreek-e-Insaf)%20vice-president%20%5BShah%20Mahmood%5D%20Qureshi%20have%20been%20sentenced%20to%2010%20years%20each%20inside%20prison%20in%20the%20cypher%20case%2C%E2%80%9D%20a%20PTI%20spokesperson%20told%20AFP.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20sentencing%20comes%20as%20Pakistan%20approaches%20elections%20slated%20for%20February%208.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWe%20will%20challenge%20today%E2%80%99s%20court%20proceedings%20before%20the%20Supreme%20Court%2C%E2%80%9D%20PTI%20Chairman%20Barrister%20Gohar%20Khan%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EImran%20Khan%E2%80%99s%20legal%20troubles%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20was%20sentenced%20to%20three%20years%20in%20August%20after%20being%20convicted%20of%20corruption%2C%20but%20a%20court%20suspended%20that%20jail%20term.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20and%20Qureshi%20have%20pleaded%20not%20guilty%20ever%20since%20being%20indicted%20for%20exposing%20state%20secrets%20in%20October.%20Khan%20was%20granted%20bail%20in%20the%20case%20in%20December.%20But%20he%20remained%20behind%20bars%20due%20to%20the%20various%20other%20legal%20troubles%20he%20was%20facing%20since%20being%20ousted%20from%20his%20position%20as%20prime%20minister%20in%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%20in%20April%202022.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%2071-year-old%20cricket%20star-turned-politician%20has%20claimed%20that%20the%20charges%20against%20him%20were%20intended%20to%20stop%20him%20from%20running%20in%20the%20upcoming%20election.%20He%20also%20said%20he%20had%20been%20targeted%20by%20a%20US-backed%20conspiracy%20over%20his%20close%20relationship%20with%20Russian%20President%20Vladimir%20Putin.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPakistan%20cypher%20controversy%3A%20A%20%E2%80%98misreading%20of%20conversation%E2%80%99%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%20remains%20one%20of%20the%20most%20popular%20politicians%20in%20Pakistan%20and%20despite%20being%20behind%20bars%20%E2%80%94%20and%20thus%20blocked%20from%20standing%20in%20the%20election%20%E2%80%94%20he%20still%20wields%20huge%20political%20power.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHis%20supporters%20have%20regularly%20protested%20in%20the%20street%2C%20but%20the%20PTI%20party%20has%20also%20faced%20its%20own%20crackdown.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20mid-January%2C%20a%20Pakistani%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20party%20must%20drop%20its%20cricket%20bat%20symbol%2C%20effectively%20forcing%20the%20candidates%20to%20run%20as%20independents%20without%20their%20famous%20symbol%20that%20had%20helped%20the%20many%20illiterate%20voters%20identify%20the%20party.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20key%20player%20in%20Pakistani%20politics%20is%20the%20powerful%20military%20that%20has%20held%20the%20reigns%20of%20power%20for%20decades%20%E2%80%94%20sometimes%20doing%20away%20with%20elections%20entirely.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EKhan%E2%80%99s%20fate%20has%20been%20tied%20to%20his%20relationship%20with%20the%20generals%20who%20once%20favored%20him%20but%20with%20whom%20he%20has%20since%20fallen%20out.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20experience%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20Nawaz%20Sharif%2C%20who%20was%20previously%20removed%20from%20power%20and%20who%20fled%20into%20exile%2C%20has%20been%20somewhat%20reversed%20as%20he%20is%20now%20considered%20the%20favorite%20in%20February%E2%80%99s%20vote%20and%20his%20past%20falling%20out%20with%20the%20military%20appears%20to%20have%20been%20forgiven.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20first%20appeared%20on%20%3C%2Fem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fpakistan-ex-pm-imran-khan-sentenced-to-10-years%2Fa-68118794%5C%22%3EDW%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cem%3E.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1706610049000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F05%2F10123703%2FScreenshot-2023-05-10-at-12.36.54-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewi